99 struct position_t
100 {
102 std::size_t chars_read_total = 0;
104 std::size_t chars_read_current_line = 0;
106 std::size_t lines_read = 0;
107
109 constexpr operator size_t() const
110 {
111 return chars_read_total;
112 }
113 };

124 // exceptions //

155 class exception : public std::exception
156 {
157 public:
159 const char* what() const noexcept override
160 {
161 return m.what();
162 }
163
165 const int id;
166
167 protected:
168 exception(int id_, const char* what_arg) : id(id_), m(what_arg) {}
169
170 static std::string name(const std::string& ename, int id_)
171 {
172 return "[json.exception." + ename + "." + std::to_string(id_) + "] ";
173 }
174
175 private:
177 std::runtime_error m;
178 };
179
224 class parse_error : public exception
225 {
226 public:
236 static parse_error create(int id_, const position_t& pos, const std::string& what_arg)
237 {
238 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
239 position_string(pos) + ": " + what_arg;
240 return parse_error(id_, pos.chars_read_total, w.c_str());
241 }
242
243 static parse_error create(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const std::string& what_arg)
244 {
245 std::string w = exception::name("parse_error", id_) + "parse error" +
246 (byte_ != 0 ? (" at byte " + std::to_string(byte_)) : "") +
247 ": " + what_arg;
248 return parse_error(id_, byte_, w.c_str());
249 }
250
260 const std::size_t byte;
261
262 private:
263 parse_error(int id_, std::size_t byte_, const char* what_arg)
264 : exception(id_, what_arg), byte(byte_) {}
265
266 static std::string position_string(const position_t& pos)
267 {
268 return " at line " + std::to_string(pos.lines_read + 1) +
269 ", column " + std::to_string(pos.chars_read_current_line);
270 }
271 };
272
310 class invalid_iterator : public exception
311 {
312 public:
313 static invalid_iterator create(int id_, const std::string& what_arg)
314 {
315 std::string w = exception::name("invalid_iterator", id_) + what_arg;
316 return invalid_iterator(id_, w.c_str());
317 }
318
319 private:
320 invalid_iterator(int id_, const char* what_arg)
321 : exception(id_, what_arg) {}
322 };
323

368 std::string w = exception::name("type_error", id_) + what_arg;
369 return type_error(id_, w.c_str());
370 }
371
372 private:
373 type_error(int id_, const char* what_arg) : exception(id_, what_arg) {}
374 };

522#define JSON_NODISCARD
523#endif

530#define JSON_THROW(exception) throw exception
531#define JSON_TRY try
532#define JSON_CATCH(exception) catch(exception)
533#define JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH(exception) catch(exception)
534#else
535#include <cstdlib>
536#define JSON_THROW(exception) std::abort()
537#define JSON_TRY if(true)

563#if defined(__clang__) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
564#define JSON_LIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(x, 1)
565#define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) __builtin_expect(x, 0)

567#define JSON_LIKELY(x) x
568#define JSON_UNLIKELY(x) x

576#define NLOHMANN_JSON_SERIALIZE_ENUM(ENUM_TYPE, ...) \
577template<typename BasicJsonType> \
578inline void to_json(BasicJsonType& j, const ENUM_TYPE& e) \
579{ \
580static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
581static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
582auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
583[e](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
584{ \
585return ej_pair.first == e; \
586}); \
587j = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->second; \
588} \
589template<typename BasicJsonType> \
590inline void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ENUM_TYPE& e) \
591{ \
592static_assert(std::is_enum<ENUM_TYPE>::value, #ENUM_TYPE " must be an enum!"); \
593static const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType> m[] = __VA_ARGS__; \
594auto it = std::find_if(std::begin(m), std::end(m), \
595[j](const std::pair<ENUM_TYPE, BasicJsonType>& ej_pair) -> bool \
596{ \
597return ej_pair.second == j; \
598}); \
599e = ((it != std::end(m)) ? it : std::begin(m))->first; \
600}

602// Ugly macros to avoid uglier copy-paste when specializing basic_json. They
603// may be removed in the future once the class is split.
604
605#define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION \
606template<template<typename, typename, typename...> class ObjectType, \
607template<typename, typename...> class ArrayType, \
608class StringType, class BooleanType, class NumberIntegerType, \
609class NumberUnsignedType, class NumberFloatType, \
610template<typename> class AllocatorType, \
611template<typename, typename = void> class JSONSerializer>
612
613#define NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL \
614basic_json<ObjectType, ArrayType, StringType, BooleanType, \
615NumberIntegerType, NumberUnsignedType, NumberFloatType, \
616AllocatorType, JSONSerializer>

629 // alias templates to reduce boilerplate
630 template<bool B, typename T = void>
631 using enable_if_t = typename std::enable_if<B, T>::type;

636 // implementation of C++14 index_sequence and affiliates
637 // source: https://stackoverflow.com/a/32223343
638 template<std::size_t... Ints>
639 struct index_sequence
640 {
641 using type = index_sequence;
642 using value_type = std::size_t;
643 static constexpr std::size_t size() noexcept
644 {
645 return sizeof...(Ints);
646 }
647 };
648
649 template<class Sequence1, class Sequence2>
650 struct merge_and_renumber;
651
652 template<std::size_t... I1, std::size_t... I2>
653 struct merge_and_renumber<index_sequence<I1...>, index_sequence<I2...>>
654 : index_sequence < I1..., (sizeof...(I1) + I2)... > {};
655
656 template<std::size_t N>
657 struct make_index_sequence
658 : merge_and_renumber < typename make_index_sequence < N / 2 >::type,
659 typename make_index_sequence < N - N / 2 >::type > {};
660
661 template<> struct make_index_sequence<0> : index_sequence<> {};
662 template<> struct make_index_sequence<1> : index_sequence<0> {};
663
664 template<typename... Ts>
665 using index_sequence_for = make_index_sequence<sizeof...(Ts)>;
666
667 // dispatch utility (taken from ranges-v3)
668 template<unsigned N> struct priority_tag : priority_tag < N - 1 > {};
669 template<> struct priority_tag<0> {};
670
671 // taken from ranges-v3
672 template<typename T>
673 struct static_const
674 {
675 static constexpr T value{};
676 };
677
678 template<typename T>
679 constexpr T static_const<T>::value;
680 } // namespace detail
681} // namespace nlohmann

718 template <typename It, typename = void>
719 struct iterator_types {};
720
721 template <typename It>
722 struct iterator_types <
723 It,
724 void_t<typename It::difference_type, typename It::value_type, typename It::pointer,
725 typename It::reference, typename It::iterator_category >>
726 {
727 using difference_type = typename It::difference_type;
728 using value_type = typename It::value_type;
729 using pointer = typename It::pointer;
730 using reference = typename It::reference;
731 using iterator_category = typename It::iterator_category;
732 };
733
734 // This is required as some compilers implement std::iterator_traits in a way that
735 // doesn't work with SFINAE. See https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1341.
736 template <typename T, typename = void>
737 struct iterator_traits
738 {
739 };
740
741 template <typename T>
742 struct iterator_traits < T, enable_if_t < !std::is_pointer<T>::value >>
743 : iterator_types<T>
744 {
745 };
746
747 template <typename T>
748 struct iterator_traits<T*, enable_if_t<std::is_object<T>::value>>
749 {
750 using iterator_category = std::random_access_iterator_tag;
751 using value_type = T;
752 using difference_type = ptrdiff_t;
753 using pointer = T*;
754 using reference = T&;
755 };
756 } // namespace detail
757} // namespace nlohmann

776 struct nonesuch
777 {
778 nonesuch() = delete;
779 ~nonesuch() = delete;
780 nonesuch(nonesuch const&) = delete;
781 nonesuch(nonesuch const&&) = delete;
782 void operator=(nonesuch const&) = delete;
783 void operator=(nonesuch&&) = delete;
784 };
785
786 template <class Default,
787 class AlwaysVoid,
788 template <class...> class Op,
789 class... Args>
790 struct detector
791 {
792 using value_t = std::false_type;
793 using type = Default;
794 };
795
796 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
797 struct detector<Default, void_t<Op<Args...>>, Op, Args...>
798 {
799 using value_t = std::true_type;
800 using type = Op<Args...>;
801 };
802
803 template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
804 using is_detected = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::value_t;
805
806 template <template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
807 using detected_t = typename detector<nonesuch, void, Op, Args...>::type;
808
809 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
810 using detected_or = detector<Default, void, Op, Args...>;
811
812 template <class Default, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
813 using detected_or_t = typename detected_or<Default, Op, Args...>::type;
814
815 template <class Expected, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
816 using is_detected_exact = std::is_same<Expected, detected_t<Op, Args...>>;
817
818 template <class To, template <class...> class Op, class... Args>
819 using is_detected_convertible =
820 std::is_convertible<detected_t<Op, Args...>, To>;
821 } // namespace detail
822} // namespace nlohmann

904 // helpers //
906
907 // Note to maintainers:
908 //
909 // Every trait in this file expects a non CV-qualified type.
910 // The only exceptions are in the 'aliases for detected' section
911 // (i.e. those of the form: decltype(T::member_function(std::declval<T>())))
912 //
913 // In this case, T has to be properly CV-qualified to constraint the function arguments
914 // (e.g. to_json(BasicJsonType&, const T&))
915
916 template<typename> struct is_basic_json : std::false_type {};
917
918 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
919 struct is_basic_json<NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL> : std::true_type {};
920
922 // aliases for detected //
924
925 template <typename T>
926 using mapped_type_t = typename T::mapped_type;
927
928 template <typename T>
929 using key_type_t = typename T::key_type;
930
931 template <typename T>
932 using value_type_t = typename T::value_type;
933
934 template <typename T>
935 using difference_type_t = typename T::difference_type;
936
937 template <typename T>
938 using pointer_t = typename T::pointer;
939
940 template <typename T>
941 using reference_t = typename T::reference;
942
943 template <typename T>
944 using iterator_category_t = typename T::iterator_category;
945
946 template <typename T>
947 using iterator_t = typename T::iterator;
948
949 template <typename T, typename... Args>
950 using to_json_function = decltype(T::to_json(std::declval<Args>()...));
951
952 template <typename T, typename... Args>
953 using from_json_function = decltype(T::from_json(std::declval<Args>()...));
954
955 template <typename T, typename U>
956 using get_template_function = decltype(std::declval<T>().template get<U>());
957
958 // trait checking if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&, udt&) exists
959 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
960 struct has_from_json : std::false_type {};
961
962 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
963 struct has_from_json<BasicJsonType, T,
964 enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>>
965 {
966 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
967
968 static constexpr bool value =
969 is_detected_exact<void, from_json_function, serializer,
970 const BasicJsonType&, T&>::value;
971 };
972
973 // This trait checks if JSONSerializer<T>::from_json(json const&) exists
974 // this overload is used for non-default-constructible user-defined-types
975 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
976 struct has_non_default_from_json : std::false_type {};
977
978 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
979 struct has_non_default_from_json<BasicJsonType, T, enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>>
980 {
981 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
982
983 static constexpr bool value =
984 is_detected_exact<T, from_json_function, serializer,
985 const BasicJsonType&>::value;
986 };
987
988 // This trait checks if BasicJsonType::json_serializer<T>::to_json exists
989 // Do not evaluate the trait when T is a basic_json type, to avoid template instantiation infinite recursion.
990 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename = void>
991 struct has_to_json : std::false_type {};
992
993 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
994 struct has_to_json<BasicJsonType, T, enable_if_t<not is_basic_json<T>::value>>
995 {
996 using serializer = typename BasicJsonType::template json_serializer<T, void>;
997
998 static constexpr bool value =
999 is_detected_exact<void, to_json_function, serializer, BasicJsonType&,
1000 T>::value;
1001 };

1008 template <typename T, typename = void>
1009 struct is_iterator_traits : std::false_type {};
1010
1011 template <typename T>
1012 struct is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<T>>
1013 {
1014 private:
1015 using traits = iterator_traits<T>;
1016
1017 public:
1018 static constexpr auto value =
1019 is_detected<value_type_t, traits>::value &&
1020 is_detected<difference_type_t, traits>::value &&
1021 is_detected<pointer_t, traits>::value &&
1022 is_detected<iterator_category_t, traits>::value &&
1023 is_detected<reference_t, traits>::value;
1024 };

1034 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType,
1035 typename = void>
1036 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1037
1038 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleObjectType>
1039 struct is_compatible_object_type_impl <
1040 BasicJsonType, CompatibleObjectType,
1041 enable_if_t<is_detected<mapped_type_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value and
1042 is_detected<key_type_t, CompatibleObjectType>::value >>
1043 {
1044
1045 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
1046
1047 // macOS's is_constructible does not play well with nonesuch...
1048 static constexpr bool value =
1049 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::key_type,
1050 typename CompatibleObjectType::key_type>::value and
1051 std::is_constructible<typename object_t::mapped_type,
1052 typename CompatibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value;
1053 };

1059 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType,
1060 typename = void>
1061 struct is_constructible_object_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1062
1063 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType>
1064 struct is_constructible_object_type_impl <
1065 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType,
1066 enable_if_t<is_detected<mapped_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value and
1067 is_detected<key_type_t, ConstructibleObjectType>::value >>
1068 {
1069 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
1070
1071 static constexpr bool value =
1072 (std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleObjectType>::value and
1073 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value or
1074 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleObjectType>::value) and
1075 (std::is_constructible<typename ConstructibleObjectType::key_type,
1076 typename object_t::key_type>::value and
1077 std::is_same <
1078 typename object_t::mapped_type,
1079 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value)) or
1080 (has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
1081 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>::value or
1082 has_non_default_from_json <
1083 BasicJsonType,
1084 typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type >::value);
1085 };

1087 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType>
1088 struct is_constructible_object_type
1089 : is_constructible_object_type_impl<BasicJsonType,
1090 ConstructibleObjectType> {};

1129 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType, typename = void>
1130 struct is_compatible_array_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1131
1132 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1133 struct is_compatible_array_type_impl <
1134 BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType,
1135 enable_if_t<is_detected<value_type_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1136 is_detected<iterator_t, CompatibleArrayType>::value and
1137 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type...
1138 // Therefore it is detected as a CompatibleArrayType.
1139 // The real fix would be to have an Iterable concept.
1140 not is_iterator_traits<
1141 iterator_traits<CompatibleArrayType>>::value >>
1142 {
1143 static constexpr bool value =
1144 std::is_constructible<BasicJsonType,
1145 typename CompatibleArrayType::value_type>::value;
1146 };
1147
1148 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleArrayType>
1149 struct is_compatible_array_type
1150 : is_compatible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleArrayType> {};
1151
1152 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType, typename = void>
1153 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1154
1155 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1156 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
1157 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
1158 enable_if_t<std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
1159 typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value >>
1160 : std::true_type {};
1161
1162 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1163 struct is_constructible_array_type_impl <
1164 BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType,
1165 enable_if_t<not std::is_same<ConstructibleArrayType,
1166 typename BasicJsonType::value_type>::value and
1167 std::is_default_constructible<ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1168 (std::is_move_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value or
1169 std::is_copy_assignable<ConstructibleArrayType>::value) and
1170 is_detected<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1171 is_detected<iterator_t, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1172 is_complete_type<
1173 detected_t<value_type_t, ConstructibleArrayType>>::value >>
1174 {
1175 static constexpr bool value =
1176 // This is needed because json_reverse_iterator has a ::iterator type,
1177 // furthermore, std::back_insert_iterator (and other iterators) have a
1178 // base class `iterator`... Therefore it is detected as a
1179 // ConstructibleArrayType. The real fix would be to have an Iterable
1180 // concept.
1181 not is_iterator_traits<iterator_traits<ConstructibleArrayType>>::value and
1182
1183 (std::is_same<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type,
1184 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type>::value or
1185 has_from_json<BasicJsonType,
1186 typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>::value or
1187 has_non_default_from_json <
1188 BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type >::value);
1189 };
1190
1191 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1192 struct is_constructible_array_type
1193 : is_constructible_array_type_impl<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType> {};

1195 template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType,
1196 typename = void>
1197 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl : std::false_type {};
1198
1199 template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
1200 struct is_compatible_integer_type_impl <
1201 RealIntegerType, CompatibleNumberIntegerType,
1202 enable_if_t<std::is_integral<RealIntegerType>::value and
1203 std::is_integral<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
1204 not std::is_same<bool, CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value >>
1205 {
1206 // is there an assert somewhere on overflows?
1207 using RealLimits = std::numeric_limits<RealIntegerType>;
1208 using CompatibleLimits = std::numeric_limits<CompatibleNumberIntegerType>;
1209
1210 static constexpr auto value =
1211 std::is_constructible<RealIntegerType,
1212 CompatibleNumberIntegerType>::value and
1213 CompatibleLimits::is_integer and
1214 RealLimits::is_signed == CompatibleLimits::is_signed;
1215 };
1216
1217 template <typename RealIntegerType, typename CompatibleNumberIntegerType>
1218 struct is_compatible_integer_type
1219 : is_compatible_integer_type_impl<RealIntegerType,
1220 CompatibleNumberIntegerType> {};
1221
1222 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleType, typename = void>
1223 struct is_compatible_type_impl: std::false_type {};
1224
1225 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleType>
1226 struct is_compatible_type_impl <
1227 BasicJsonType, CompatibleType,
1228 enable_if_t<is_complete_type<CompatibleType>::value >>
1229 {
1230 static constexpr bool value =
1231 has_to_json<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType>::value;
1232 };

1234 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename CompatibleType>
1235 struct is_compatible_type
1236 : is_compatible_type_impl<BasicJsonType, CompatibleType> {};

1240// #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
1241
1242
1243#include <array> // array
1244#include <ciso646> // and
1245#include <cstddef> // size_t
1246#include <cstdint> // uint8_t
1247#include <string> // string
1248
1249namespace nlohmann
1250{
1251 namespace detail
1252 {
1254 // JSON type enumeration //
1256
1281 enum class value_t : std::uint8_t
1282 {
1283 null,
1284 object,
1285 array,
1286 string,
1287 boolean,
1288 number_integer,
1289 number_unsigned,
1290 number_float,
1291 discarded
1292 };
1293
1304 inline bool operator<(const value_t lhs, const value_t rhs) noexcept
1305 {
1306 static constexpr std::array<std::uint8_t, 8> order = {{
1307 0 /* null */, 3 /* object */, 4 /* array */, 5 /* string */,
1308 1 /* boolean */, 2 /* integer */, 2 /* unsigned */, 2 /* float */
1309 }
1310 };
1311
1312 const auto l_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(lhs);
1313 const auto r_index = static_cast<std::size_t>(rhs);
1314 return l_index < order.size() and r_index < order.size() and order[l_index] < order[r_index];
1315 }
1316 } // namespace detail
1317} // namespace nlohmann

1322 namespace detail

1324 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1325 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, typename std::nullptr_t& n)
1326 {
1327 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_null()))
1328 {
1329 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be null, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1330 }
1331 n = nullptr;
1332 }
1333
1334 // overloads for basic_json template parameters
1335 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1336 enable_if_t<std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1337 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1338 int> = 0>
1339 void get_arithmetic_value(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1340 {
1341 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1342 {
1343 case value_t::number_unsigned:
1344 {
1345 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1346 break;
1347 }
1348 case value_t::number_integer:
1349 {
1350 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1351 break;
1352 }
1353 case value_t::number_float:
1354 {
1355 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1356 break;
1357 }
1358
1359 default:
1360 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1361 }
1362 }
1363

1369 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be boolean, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1370 }
1371 b = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>();
1372 }

1428 // forward_list doesn't have an insert method
1429 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T, typename Allocator,
1430 enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1431 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::forward_list<T, Allocator>& l)
1432 {
1433 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1434 {
1435 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1436 }
1437 l.clear();
1438 std::transform(j.rbegin(), j.rend(),
1439 std::front_inserter(l), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1440 {
1441 return i.template get<T>();
1442 });
1443 }
1444
1445 // valarray doesn't have an insert method
1446 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T,
1447 enable_if_t<std::is_convertible<BasicJsonType, T>::value, int> = 0>
1448 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::valarray<T>& l)
1449 {
1450 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1451 {
1452 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1453 }
1454 l.resize(j.size());
1455 std::copy(j.m_value.array->begin(), j.m_value.array->end(), std::begin(l));
1456 }

1458 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1459 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, T (&arr)[N])
1460 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void())
1461 {
1462 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1463 {
1464 arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1465 }
1466 }

1468 template<typename BasicJsonType>
1469 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, typename BasicJsonType::array_t& arr, priority_tag<3> /*unused*/)
1470 {
1471 arr = *j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::array_t*>();
1472 }
1473
1474 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename T, std::size_t N>
1475 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, std::array<T, N>& arr,
1476 priority_tag<2> /*unused*/)
1477 -> decltype(j.template get<T>(), void())
1478 {
1479 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < N; ++i)
1480 {
1481 arr[i] = j.at(i).template get<T>();
1482 }
1483 }
1484
1485 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1486 auto from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr, priority_tag<1> /*unused*/)
1487 -> decltype(
1488 arr.reserve(std::declval<typename ConstructibleArrayType::size_type>()),
1489 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
1490 void())
1491 {
1492 using std::end;
1493
1494 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
1495 ret.reserve(j.size());
1496 std::transform(j.begin(), j.end(),
1497 std::inserter(ret, end(ret)), [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1498 {
1499 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1500 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1501 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
1502 });
1503 arr = std::move(ret);
1504 }
1505
1506 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType>
1507 void from_json_array_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr,
1508 priority_tag<0> /*unused*/)
1509 {
1510 using std::end;
1511
1512 ConstructibleArrayType ret;
1513 std::transform(
1514 j.begin(), j.end(), std::inserter(ret, end(ret)),
1515 [](const BasicJsonType & i)
1516 {
1517 // get<BasicJsonType>() returns *this, this won't call a from_json
1518 // method when value_type is BasicJsonType
1519 return i.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>();
1520 });
1521 arr = std::move(ret);
1522 }
1523
1524 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleArrayType,
1525 enable_if_t <
1526 is_constructible_array_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1527 not is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1528 not is_constructible_string_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleArrayType>::value and
1529 not is_basic_json<ConstructibleArrayType>::value,
1530 int > = 0 >
1531
1532 auto from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleArrayType& arr)
1533 -> decltype(from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {}),
1534 j.template get<typename ConstructibleArrayType::value_type>(),
1535 void())
1536 {
1537 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1538 {
1539 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " +
1540 std::string(j.type_name())));
1541 }
1542
1543 from_json_array_impl(j, arr, priority_tag<3> {});
1544 }
1545
1546 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ConstructibleObjectType,
1547 enable_if_t<is_constructible_object_type<BasicJsonType, ConstructibleObjectType>::value, int> = 0>
1548 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ConstructibleObjectType& obj)
1549 {
1550 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_object()))
1551 {
1552 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1553 }
1554
1555 ConstructibleObjectType ret;
1556 auto inner_object = j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::object_t*>();
1557 using value_type = typename ConstructibleObjectType::value_type;
1558 std::transform(
1559 inner_object->begin(), inner_object->end(),
1560 std::inserter(ret, ret.begin()),
1561 [](typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type const & p)
1562 {
1563 return value_type(p.first, p.second.template get<typename ConstructibleObjectType::mapped_type>());
1564 });
1565 obj = std::move(ret);
1566 }
1567
1568 // overload for arithmetic types, not chosen for basic_json template arguments
1569 // (BooleanType, etc..); note: Is it really necessary to provide explicit
1570 // overloads for boolean_t etc. in case of a custom BooleanType which is not
1571 // an arithmetic type?
1572 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename ArithmeticType,
1573 enable_if_t <
1574 std::is_arithmetic<ArithmeticType>::value and
1575 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t>::value and
1576 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t>::value and
1577 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t>::value and
1578 not std::is_same<ArithmeticType, typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t>::value,
1579 int> = 0>
1580 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, ArithmeticType& val)
1581 {
1582 switch (static_cast<value_t>(j))
1583 {
1584 case value_t::number_unsigned:
1585 {
1586 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t*>());
1587 break;
1588 }
1589 case value_t::number_integer:
1590 {
1591 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t*>());
1592 break;
1593 }
1594 case value_t::number_float:
1595 {
1596 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t*>());
1597 break;
1598 }
1599 case value_t::boolean:
1600 {
1601 val = static_cast<ArithmeticType>(*j.template get_ptr<const typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t*>());
1602 break;
1603 }
1604
1605 default:
1606 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be number, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1607 }
1608 }
1609
1610 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename A1, typename A2>
1611 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::pair<A1, A2>& p)
1612 {
1613 p = {j.at(0).template get<A1>(), j.at(1).template get<A2>()};
1614 }

1616 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename Tuple, std::size_t... Idx>
1617 void from_json_tuple_impl(const BasicJsonType& j, Tuple& t, index_sequence<Idx...> /*unused*/)
1618 {
1619 t = std::make_tuple(j.at(Idx).template get<typename std::tuple_element<Idx, Tuple>::type>()...);
1620 }
1621
1622 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename... Args>
1623 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::tuple<Args...>& t)
1624 {
1625 from_json_tuple_impl(j, t, index_sequence_for<Args...> {});
1626 }
1627
1628 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Compare, typename Allocator,
1629 typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1630 typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1631 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::map<Key, Value, Compare, Allocator>& m)
1632 {
1633 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1634 {
1635 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1636 }
1637 m.clear();
1638 for (const auto& p : j)
1639 {
1640 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1641 {
1642 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1643 }
1644 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1645 }
1646 }
1647
1648 template <typename BasicJsonType, typename Key, typename Value, typename Hash, typename KeyEqual, typename Allocator,
1649 typename = enable_if_t<not std::is_constructible<
1650 typename BasicJsonType::string_t, Key>::value>>
1651 void from_json(const BasicJsonType& j, std::unordered_map<Key, Value, Hash, KeyEqual, Allocator>& m)
1652 {
1653 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not j.is_array()))
1654 {
1655 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
1656 }
1657 m.clear();
1658 for (const auto& p : j)
1659 {
1660 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not p.is_array()))
1661 {
1662 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(302, "type must be array, but is " + std::string(p.type_name())));
1663 }
1664 m.emplace(p.at(0).template get<Key>(), p.at(1).template get<Value>());
1665 }
1666 }
1667
1668 struct from_json_fn
1669 {
1670 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename T>
1671 auto operator()(const BasicJsonType& j, T& val) const
1672 noexcept(noexcept(from_json(j, val)))
1673 -> decltype(from_json(j, val), void())
1674 {
1675 return from_json(j, val);
1676 }
1677 };
1678 } // namespace detail
1679
1683 namespace
1684 {
1685 constexpr const auto& from_json = detail::static_const<detail::from_json_fn>::value;
1686 } // namespace
1687} // namespace nlohmann

1718 {
1719 template <typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value
1720 {
1721 public:
1722 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
1723 using value_type = iteration_proxy_value;
1724 using pointer = value_type * ;
1725 using reference = value_type & ;
1726 using iterator_category = std::input_iterator_tag;
1727
1728 private:
1730 IteratorType anchor;
1732 std::size_t array_index = 0;
1734 mutable std::size_t array_index_last = 0;
1736 mutable std::string array_index_str = "0";
1738 const std::string empty_str = "";
1739
1740 public:
1741 explicit iteration_proxy_value(IteratorType it) noexcept : anchor(it) {}
1742
1744 iteration_proxy_value& operator*()
1745 {
1746 return *this;
1747 }
1748
1750 iteration_proxy_value& operator++()
1751 {
1752 ++anchor;
1753 ++array_index;
1754
1755 return *this;
1756 }
1757
1759 bool operator==(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
1760 {
1761 return anchor == o.anchor;
1762 }
1763
1765 bool operator!=(const iteration_proxy_value& o) const
1766 {
1767 return anchor != o.anchor;
1768 }
1769
1771 const std::string& key() const
1772 {
1773 assert(anchor.m_object != nullptr);
1774
1775 switch (anchor.m_object->type())
1776 {
1777 // use integer array index as key
1778 case value_t::array:
1779 {
1780 if (array_index != array_index_last)
1781 {
1782 array_index_str = std::to_string(array_index);
1783 array_index_last = array_index;
1784 }
1785 return array_index_str;
1786 }
1787
1788 // use key from the object
1789 case value_t::object:
1790 return anchor.key();
1791
1792 // use an empty key for all primitive types
1793 default:
1794 return empty_str;
1795 }
1796 }
1797
1799 typename IteratorType::reference value() const
1800 {
1801 return anchor.value();
1802 }
1803 };
1804
1806 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy
1807 {
1808 private:
1810 typename IteratorType::reference container;
1811
1812 public:
1814 explicit iteration_proxy(typename IteratorType::reference cont) noexcept
1815 : container(cont) {}
1816
1818 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> begin() noexcept
1819 {
1820 return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.begin());
1821 }
1822
1824 iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType> end() noexcept
1825 {
1826 return iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>(container.end());
1827 }
1828 };
1829 // Structured Bindings Support
1830 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
1831 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
1832 template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 0, int> = 0>
1833 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.key())
1834 {
1835 return i.key();
1836 }
1837 // Structured Bindings Support
1838 // For further reference see https://blog.tartanllama.xyz/structured-bindings/
1839 // And see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/1391
1840 template <std::size_t N, typename IteratorType, enable_if_t<N == 1, int> = 0>
1841 auto get(const nlohmann::detail::iteration_proxy_value<IteratorType>& i) -> decltype(i.value())
1842 {
1843 return i.value();
1844 }
1845 } // namespace detail
1846} // namespace nlohmann

1861 : public std::integral_constant<std::size_t, 2> {};

1868 get<N>(std::declval <

2005 j.m_type = value_t::array;
2006 j.m_value = value_t::array;
2007 j.m_value.array->reserve(arr.size());
2008 for (const bool x : arr)
2009 {
2010 j.m_value.array->push_back(x);
2011 }
2012 j.assert_invariant();
2013 }

2018 {
2019 j.m_type = value_t::array;
2020 j.m_value = value_t::array;
2021 j.m_value.array->resize(arr.size());
2022 std::copy(std::begin(arr), std::end(arr), j.m_value.array->begin());
2023 j.assert_invariant();
2024 }

2373 ~input_stream_adapter() override
2374 {
2375 // clear stream flags; we use underlying streambuf I/O, do not
2376 // maintain ifstream flags, except eof
2377 is.clear(is.rdstate() & std::ios::eofbit);
2378 }
2379
2380 explicit input_stream_adapter(std::istream& i)
2381 : is(i), sb(*i.rdbuf())
2382 {}
2383
2384 // delete because of pointer members
2385 input_stream_adapter(const input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
2386 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&) = delete;
2387 input_stream_adapter(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
2388 input_stream_adapter& operator=(input_stream_adapter&&) = delete;
2389
2390 // std::istream/std::streambuf use std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type, to
2391 // ensure that std::char_traits<char>::eof() and the character 0xFF do not
2392 // end up as the same value, eg. 0xFFFFFFFF.
2393 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() override
2394 {
2395 auto res = sb.sbumpc();
2396 // set eof manually, as we don't use the istream interface.
2397 if (res == EOF)
2398 {
2399 is.clear(is.rdstate() | std::ios::eofbit);
2400 }
2401 return res;
2402 }
2403
2404 private:
2406 std::istream& is;
2407 std::streambuf& sb;
2408 };
2409
2411 class input_buffer_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2412 {
2413 public:
2414 input_buffer_adapter(const char* b, const std::size_t l) noexcept
2415 : cursor(b), limit(b + l)
2416 {}
2417
2418 // delete because of pointer members
2419 input_buffer_adapter(const input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
2420 input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&) = delete;
2421 input_buffer_adapter(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
2422 input_buffer_adapter& operator=(input_buffer_adapter&&) = delete;
2423 ~input_buffer_adapter() override = default;
2424
2425 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
2426 {
2427 if (JSON_LIKELY(cursor < limit))
2428 {
2429 return std::char_traits<char>::to_int_type(*(cursor++));
2430 }
2431
2432 return std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2433 }
2434
2435 private:
2437 const char* cursor;
2439 const char* const limit;
2440 };
2441
2442 template<typename WideStringType, size_t T>
2443 struct wide_string_input_helper
2444 {
2445 // UTF-32
2446 static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str,
2447 size_t& current_wchar,
2448 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
2449 size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
2450 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
2451 {
2452 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2453
2454 if (current_wchar == str.size())
2455 {
2456 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2457 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2458 }
2459 else
2460 {
2461 // get the current character
2462 const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2463
2464 // UTF-32 to UTF-8 encoding
2465 if (wc < 0x80)
2466 {
2467 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2468 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2469 }
2470 else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
2471 {
2472 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x1Fu));
2473 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2474 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
2475 }
2476 else if (wc <= 0xFFFF)
2477 {
2478 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x0Fu));
2479 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2480 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2481 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2482 }
2483 else if (wc <= 0x10FFFF)
2484 {
2485 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | ((wc >> 18u) & 0x07u));
2486 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
2487 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2488 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2489 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2490 }
2491 else
2492 {
2493 // unknown character
2494 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2495 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2496 }
2497 }
2498 }
2499 };
2500
2501 template<typename WideStringType>
2502 struct wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, 2>
2503 {
2504 // UTF-16
2505 static void fill_buffer(const WideStringType& str,
2506 size_t& current_wchar,
2507 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4>& utf8_bytes,
2508 size_t& utf8_bytes_index,
2509 size_t& utf8_bytes_filled)
2510 {
2511 utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2512
2513 if (current_wchar == str.size())
2514 {
2515 utf8_bytes[0] = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
2516 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2517 }
2518 else
2519 {
2520 // get the current character
2521 const auto wc = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2522
2523 // UTF-16 to UTF-8 encoding
2524 if (wc < 0x80)
2525 {
2526 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2527 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2528 }
2529 else if (wc <= 0x7FF)
2530 {
2531 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xC0u | ((wc >> 6u)));
2532 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2533 utf8_bytes_filled = 2;
2534 }
2535 else if (0xD800 > wc or wc >= 0xE000)
2536 {
2537 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xE0u | ((wc >> 12u)));
2538 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((wc >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2539 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (wc & 0x3Fu));
2540 utf8_bytes_filled = 3;
2541 }
2542 else
2543 {
2544 if (current_wchar < str.size())
2545 {
2546 const auto wc2 = static_cast<unsigned int>(str[current_wchar++]);
2547 const auto charcode = 0x10000u + (((wc & 0x3FFu) << 10u) | (wc2 & 0x3FFu));
2548 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0xF0u | (charcode >> 18u));
2549 utf8_bytes[1] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 12u) & 0x3Fu));
2550 utf8_bytes[2] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | ((charcode >> 6u) & 0x3Fu));
2551 utf8_bytes[3] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(0x80u | (charcode & 0x3Fu));
2552 utf8_bytes_filled = 4;
2553 }
2554 else
2555 {
2556 // unknown character
2557 ++current_wchar;
2558 utf8_bytes[0] = static_cast<std::char_traits<char>::int_type>(wc);
2559 utf8_bytes_filled = 1;
2560 }
2561 }
2562 }
2563 }
2564 };
2565
2566 template<typename WideStringType>
2567 class wide_string_input_adapter : public input_adapter_protocol
2568 {
2569 public:
2570 explicit wide_string_input_adapter(const WideStringType& w) noexcept
2571 : str(w)
2572 {}
2573
2574 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get_character() noexcept override
2575 {
2576 // check if buffer needs to be filled
2577 if (utf8_bytes_index == utf8_bytes_filled)
2578 {
2579 fill_buffer<sizeof(typename WideStringType::value_type)>();
2580
2581 assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
2582 assert(utf8_bytes_index == 0);
2583 }
2584
2585 // use buffer
2586 assert(utf8_bytes_filled > 0);
2587 assert(utf8_bytes_index < utf8_bytes_filled);
2588 return utf8_bytes[utf8_bytes_index++];
2589 }
2590
2591 private:
2592 template<size_t T>
2593 void fill_buffer()
2594 {
2595 wide_string_input_helper<WideStringType, T>::fill_buffer(str, current_wchar, utf8_bytes, utf8_bytes_index, utf8_bytes_filled);
2596 }
2597
2599 const WideStringType& str;
2600
2602 std::size_t current_wchar = 0;
2603
2605 std::array<std::char_traits<char>::int_type, 4> utf8_bytes = {{0, 0, 0, 0}};
2606
2608 std::size_t utf8_bytes_index = 0;
2610 std::size_t utf8_bytes_filled = 0;
2611 };

2613 class input_adapter
2614 {
2615 public:

2617 input_adapter(std::FILE* file)
2618 : ia(std::make_shared<file_input_adapter>(file)) {}
2620 input_adapter(std::istream& i)
2621 : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2622
2624 input_adapter(std::istream&& i)
2625 : ia(std::make_shared<input_stream_adapter>(i)) {}
2626

2628 : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::wstring>>(ws)) {}
2629
2630 input_adapter(const std::u16string& ws)
2631 : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u16string>>(ws)) {}
2632
2633 input_adapter(const std::u32string& ws)
2634 : ia(std::make_shared<wide_string_input_adapter<std::u32string>>(ws)) {}
2635
2637 template<typename CharT,
2638 typename std::enable_if<
2639 std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2640 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2641 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2642 int>::type = 0>
2643 input_adapter(CharT b, std::size_t l)
2644 : ia(std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b), l)) {}
2645
2646 // derived support
2647
2649 template<typename CharT,
2650 typename std::enable_if<
2651 std::is_pointer<CharT>::value and
2652 std::is_integral<typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type>::value and
2653 sizeof(typename std::remove_pointer<CharT>::type) == 1,
2654 int>::type = 0>
2655 input_adapter(CharT b)
2656 : input_adapter(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b),
2657 std::strlen(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(b))) {}
2658
2660 template<class IteratorType,
2661 typename std::enable_if<
2662 std::is_same<typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::iterator_category, std::random_access_iterator_tag>::value,
2663 int>::type = 0>
2664 input_adapter(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
2665 {
2666#ifndef NDEBUG
2667 // assertion to check that the iterator range is indeed contiguous,
2668 // see http://stackoverflow.com/a/35008842/266378 for more discussion
2669 const auto is_contiguous = std::accumulate(
2670 first, last, std::pair<bool, int>(true, 0),
2671 [&first](std::pair<bool, int> res, decltype(*first) val)
2672 {
2673 res.first &= (val == *(std::next(std::addressof(*first), res.second++)));
2674 return res;
2675 }).first;
2676 assert(is_contiguous);
2677#endif
2678
2679 // assertion to check that each element is 1 byte long
2680 static_assert(
2681 sizeof(typename iterator_traits<IteratorType>::value_type) == 1,
2682 "each element in the iterator range must have the size of 1 byte");
2683
2684 const auto len = static_cast<size_t>(std::distance(first, last));
2685 if (JSON_LIKELY(len > 0))
2686 {
2687 // there is at least one element: use the address of first
2688 ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(&(*first)), len);
2689 }
2690 else
2691 {
2692 // the address of first cannot be used: use nullptr
2693 ia = std::make_shared<input_buffer_adapter>(nullptr, len);
2694 }
2695 }
2696
2698 template<class T, std::size_t N>
2699 input_adapter(T (&array)[N])
2700 : input_adapter(std::begin(array), std::end(array)) {}
2701
2703 template<class ContiguousContainer, typename
2704 std::enable_if<not std::is_pointer<ContiguousContainer>::value and
2705 std::is_base_of<std::random_access_iterator_tag, typename iterator_traits<decltype(std::begin(std::declval<ContiguousContainer const>()))>::iterator_category>::value,
2706 int>::type = 0>
2707 input_adapter(const ContiguousContainer& c)
2708 : input_adapter(std::begin(c), std::end(c)) {}
2709
2710 operator input_adapter_t()
2711 {
2712 return ia;
2713 }
2714
2715 private:
2717 input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
2718 };

2974 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
2975 const detail::exception& ex)
2976 {
2977 errored = true;
2978 if (allow_exceptions)
2979 {
2980 // determine the proper exception type from the id
2981 switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
2982 {
2983 case 1:
2984 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
2985 case 4:
2986 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
2987 // LCOV_EXCL_START
2988 case 2:
2989 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
2990 case 3:
2991 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
2992 case 5:
2993 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
2994 default:
2995 assert(false);
2996 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
2997 }
2998 }
2999 return false;

3014 template<typename Value>
3015 BasicJsonType* handle_value(Value&& v)
3016 {
3017 if (ref_stack.empty())
3018 {
3019 root = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3020 return &root;
3021 }
3022
3023 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3024
3025 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3026 {
3027 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Value>(v));
3028 return &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back());
3029 }
3030
3031 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3032 assert(object_element);
3033 *object_element = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3034 return object_element;
3035 }
3036

3040 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
3042 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
3044 bool errored = false;

3049 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3050 class json_sax_dom_callback_parser
3051 {
3052 public:
3053 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3054 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3055 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3056 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3057 using parser_callback_t = typename BasicJsonType::parser_callback_t;
3058 using parse_event_t = typename BasicJsonType::parse_event_t;
3059
3060 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(BasicJsonType& r,
3061 const parser_callback_t cb,
3062 const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
3063 : root(r), callback(cb), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
3064 {
3065 keep_stack.push_back(true);
3066 }
3067
3068 // make class move-only
3069 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
3070 json_sax_dom_callback_parser(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
3071 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(const json_sax_dom_callback_parser&) = delete;
3072 json_sax_dom_callback_parser& operator=(json_sax_dom_callback_parser&&) = default;
3073 ~json_sax_dom_callback_parser() = default;
3074
3075 bool null()
3076 {
3077 handle_value(nullptr);
3078 return true;
3079 }
3080
3081 bool boolean(bool val)
3082 {
3083 handle_value(val);
3084 return true;
3085 }
3086
3087 bool number_integer(number_integer_t val)
3088 {
3089 handle_value(val);
3090 return true;
3091 }
3092
3093 bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t val)
3094 {
3095 handle_value(val);
3096 return true;

3100 {
3101 handle_value(val);
3102 return true;

3105 bool string(string_t& val)
3106 {
3107 handle_value(val);
3108 return true;

3110
3111 bool start_object(std::size_t len)
3112 {
3113 // check callback for object start
3114 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::object_start, discarded);
3115 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3116
3117 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::object, true);
3118 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3119
3120 // check object limit
3121 if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3122 {
3123 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive object size: " + std::to_string(len)));
3124 }
3125
3126 return true;
3127 }
3128
3129 bool key(string_t& val)
3130 {
3131 BasicJsonType k = BasicJsonType(val);
3132
3133 // check callback for key
3134 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::key, k);
3135 key_keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3136
3137 // add discarded value at given key and store the reference for later
3138 if (keep and ref_stack.back())
3139 {
3140 object_element = &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.object->operator[](val) = discarded);
3141 }
3142
3143 return true;
3144 }
3145
3146 bool end_object()
3147 {
3148 if (ref_stack.back() and not callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::object_end, *ref_stack.back()))
3149 {
3150 // discard object
3151 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
3152 }
3153
3154 assert(not ref_stack.empty());
3155 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3156 ref_stack.pop_back();
3157 keep_stack.pop_back();
3158
3159 if (not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back() and ref_stack.back()->is_object())
3160 {
3161 // remove discarded value
3162 for (auto it = ref_stack.back()->begin(); it != ref_stack.back()->end(); ++it)
3163 {
3164 if (it->is_discarded())
3165 {
3166 ref_stack.back()->erase(it);
3167 break;
3168 }
3169 }
3170 }
3171
3172 return true;
3173 }
3174
3175 bool start_array(std::size_t len)
3176 {
3177 const bool keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::array_start, discarded);
3178 keep_stack.push_back(keep);
3179
3180 auto val = handle_value(BasicJsonType::value_t::array, true);
3181 ref_stack.push_back(val.second);
3182
3183 // check array limit
3184 if (ref_stack.back() and JSON_UNLIKELY(len != std::size_t(-1) and len > ref_stack.back()->max_size()))
3185 {
3186 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(408, "excessive array size: " + std::to_string(len)));
3187 }
3188
3189 return true;
3190 }
3191
3192 bool end_array()
3193 {
3194 bool keep = true;
3195
3196 if (ref_stack.back())
3197 {
3198 keep = callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()) - 1, parse_event_t::array_end, *ref_stack.back());
3199 if (not keep)
3200 {
3201 // discard array
3202 *ref_stack.back() = discarded;
3203 }
3204 }
3205
3206 assert(not ref_stack.empty());
3207 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3208 ref_stack.pop_back();
3209 keep_stack.pop_back();
3210
3211 // remove discarded value
3212 if (not keep and not ref_stack.empty() and ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3213 {
3214 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->pop_back();
3215 }
3216
3217 return true;
3218 }
3219
3220 bool parse_error(std::size_t /*unused*/, const std::string& /*unused*/,
3221 const detail::exception& ex)
3222 {
3223 errored = true;
3224 if (allow_exceptions)
3225 {
3226 // determine the proper exception type from the id
3227 switch ((ex.id / 100) % 100)
3228 {
3229 case 1:
3230 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::parse_error*>(&ex));
3231 case 4:
3232 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::out_of_range*>(&ex));
3233 // LCOV_EXCL_START
3234 case 2:
3235 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::invalid_iterator*>(&ex));
3236 case 3:
3237 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::type_error*>(&ex));
3238 case 5:
3239 JSON_THROW(*static_cast<const detail::other_error*>(&ex));
3240 default:
3241 assert(false);
3242 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
3243 }
3244 }
3245 return false;
3246 }
3247
3248 constexpr bool is_errored() const
3249 {
3250 return errored;
3251 }
3252
3253 private:
3269 template<typename Value>
3270 std::pair<bool, BasicJsonType*> handle_value(Value&& v, const bool skip_callback = false)
3271 {
3272 assert(not keep_stack.empty());
3273
3274 // do not handle this value if we know it would be added to a discarded
3275 // container
3276 if (not keep_stack.back())
3277 {
3278 return {false, nullptr};
3279 }
3280
3281 // create value
3282 auto value = BasicJsonType(std::forward<Value>(v));
3283
3284 // check callback
3285 const bool keep = skip_callback or callback(static_cast<int>(ref_stack.size()), parse_event_t::value, value);
3286
3287 // do not handle this value if we just learnt it shall be discarded
3288 if (not keep)
3289 {
3290 return {false, nullptr};
3291 }
3292
3293 if (ref_stack.empty())
3294 {
3295 root = std::move(value);
3296 return {true, &root};
3297 }
3298
3299 // skip this value if we already decided to skip the parent
3300 // (https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/971#issuecomment-413678360)
3301 if (not ref_stack.back())
3302 {
3303 return {false, nullptr};
3304 }
3305
3306 // we now only expect arrays and objects
3307 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_array() or ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3308
3309 // array
3310 if (ref_stack.back()->is_array())
3311 {
3312 ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->push_back(std::move(value));
3313 return {true, &(ref_stack.back()->m_value.array->back())};
3314 }
3315
3316 // object
3317 assert(ref_stack.back()->is_object());
3318 // check if we should store an element for the current key
3319 assert(not key_keep_stack.empty());
3320 const bool store_element = key_keep_stack.back();
3321 key_keep_stack.pop_back();
3322
3323 if (not store_element)
3324 {
3325 return {false, nullptr};
3326 }
3327
3328 assert(object_element);
3329 *object_element = std::move(value);
3330 return {true, object_element};
3331 }
3332
3334 BasicJsonType& root;
3336 std::vector<BasicJsonType*> ref_stack {};
3338 std::vector<bool> keep_stack {};
3340 std::vector<bool> key_keep_stack {};
3342 BasicJsonType* object_element = nullptr;
3344 bool errored = false;
3346 const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
3348 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
3350 BasicJsonType discarded = BasicJsonType::value_t::discarded;
3351 };
3352
3353 template<typename BasicJsonType>
3354 class json_sax_acceptor
3355 {
3356 public:
3357 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3358 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3359 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3360 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3361
3362 bool null()
3363 {
3364 return true;
3365 }
3366
3367 bool boolean(bool /*unused*/)
3368 {
3369 return true;
3370 }

3375 }

3378 {
3379 return true;
3380 }
3381
3382 bool number_float(number_float_t /*unused*/, const string_t& /*unused*/)
3383 {
3384 return true;
3385 }

3388 {
3389 return true;
3390 }

3393 {
3394 return true;
3395 }
3396
3397 bool key(string_t& /*unused*/)
3398 {
3399 return true;
3400 }
3401
3402 bool end_object()
3403 {
3404 return true;
3405 }
3406

3408 {
3409 return true;
3410 }
3411

3413 {

3415 }

3444 template <typename T>
3445 using null_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().null());
3446
3447 template <typename T>
3448 using boolean_function_t =
3449 decltype(std::declval<T&>().boolean(std::declval<bool>()));
3450
3451 template <typename T, typename Integer>
3452 using number_integer_function_t =
3453 decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_integer(std::declval<Integer>()));
3454
3455 template <typename T, typename Unsigned>
3456 using number_unsigned_function_t =
3457 decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_unsigned(std::declval<Unsigned>()));
3458
3459 template <typename T, typename Float, typename String>
3460 using number_float_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_float(
3461 std::declval<Float>(), std::declval<const String&>()));
3462
3463 template <typename T, typename String>
3464 using string_function_t =
3465 decltype(std::declval<T&>().string(std::declval<String&>()));
3466
3467 template <typename T>
3468 using start_object_function_t =
3469 decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_object(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
3470
3471 template <typename T, typename String>
3472 using key_function_t =
3473 decltype(std::declval<T&>().key(std::declval<String&>()));
3474
3475 template <typename T>
3476 using end_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_object());
3477
3478 template <typename T>
3479 using start_array_function_t =
3480 decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_array(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
3481
3482 template <typename T>
3483 using end_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_array());
3484
3485 template <typename T, typename Exception>
3486 using parse_error_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().parse_error(
3487 std::declval<std::size_t>(), std::declval<const std::string&>(),
3488 std::declval<const Exception&>()));

3490 template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
3491 struct is_sax
3492 {
3493 private:
3494 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
3495 "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
3496
3497 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3498 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3499 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3500 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3501 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
3502
3503 public:
3504 static constexpr bool value =
3505 is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3506 is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3507 is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
3508 number_integer_t>::value &&
3509 is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
3510 number_unsigned_t>::value &&
3511 is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t,
3512 string_t>::value &&
3513 is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
3514 is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3515 is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
3516 is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3517 is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3518 is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
3519 is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value;
3520 };
3521
3522 template <typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
3523 struct is_sax_static_asserts
3524 {
3525 private:
3526 static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
3527 "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
3528
3529 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3530 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3531 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3532 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3533 using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
3534
3535 public:
3536 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value,
3537 "Missing/invalid function: bool null()");
3538 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
3539 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
3540 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
3541 "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
3542 static_assert(
3543 is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
3544 number_integer_t>::value,
3545 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_integer(number_integer_t)");
3546 static_assert(
3547 is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
3548 number_unsigned_t>::value,
3549 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t)");
3550 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX,
3551 number_float_t, string_t>::value,
3552 "Missing/invalid function: bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&)");
3553 static_assert(
3554 is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
3555 "Missing/invalid function: bool string(string_t&)");
3556 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
3557 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_object(std::size_t)");
3558 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
3559 "Missing/invalid function: bool key(string_t&)");
3560 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
3561 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_object()");
3562 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
3563 "Missing/invalid function: bool start_array(std::size_t)");
3564 static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
3565 "Missing/invalid function: bool end_array()");
3566 static_assert(
3567 is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value,
3568 "Missing/invalid function: bool parse_error(std::size_t, const "
3569 "std::string&, const exception&)");
3570 };
