3582 // binary reader //
3584
3588 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename SAX = json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType>>
3589 class binary_reader
3590 {
3591 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
3592 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
3593 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
3594 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
3595 using json_sax_t = SAX;
3596
3597 public:
3603 explicit binary_reader(input_adapter_t adapter) : ia(std::move(adapter))
3604 {
3605 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
3606 assert(ia);
3607 }
3608
3609 // make class move-only
3610 binary_reader(const binary_reader&) = delete;
3611 binary_reader(binary_reader&&) = default;
3612 binary_reader& operator=(const binary_reader&) = delete;
3613 binary_reader& operator=(binary_reader&&) = default;
3614 ~binary_reader() = default;
3615
3623 bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format,
3624 json_sax_t* sax_,
3625 const bool strict = true)
3626 {
3627 sax = sax_;
3628 bool result = false;
3629
3630 switch (format)
3631 {
3632 case input_format_t::bson:
3633 result = parse_bson_internal();
3634 break;
3635
3636 case input_format_t::cbor:
3637 result = parse_cbor_internal();
3638 break;
3639
3640 case input_format_t::msgpack:
3641 result = parse_msgpack_internal();
3642 break;
3643
3644 case input_format_t::ubjson:
3645 result = parse_ubjson_internal();
3646 break;
3647
3648 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3649 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
3650 }
3651
3652 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
3653 if (result and strict)
3654 {
3655 if (format == input_format_t::ubjson)
3656 {
3657 get_ignore_noop();
3658 }
3659 else
3660 {
3661 get();
3662 }
3663
3664 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
3665 {
3666 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(),
3667 parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "expected end of input; last byte: 0x" + get_token_string(), "value")));
3668 }
3669 }
3670
3671 return result;
3672 }
3673
3681 static constexpr bool little_endianess(int num = 1) noexcept
3682 {
3683 return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&num) == 1;
3684 }
3685
3686 private:
3688 // BSON //
3690
3695 bool parse_bson_internal()
3696 {
3697 std::int32_t document_size;
3698 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
3699
3700 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
3701 {
3702 return false;
3703 }
3704
3705 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/false)))
3706 {
3707 return false;
3708 }
3709
3710 return sax->end_object();
3711 }
3712
3720 bool get_bson_cstr(string_t& result)
3721 {
3722 auto out = std::back_inserter(result);
3723 while (true)
3724 {
3725 get();
3726 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "cstring")))
3727 {
3728 return false;
3729 }
3730 if (current == 0x00)
3731 {
3732 return true;
3733 }
3734 *out++ = static_cast<char>(current);
3735 }
3736
3737 return true;
3738 }
3739
3751 template<typename NumberType>
3752 bool get_bson_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result)
3753 {
3754 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(len < 1))
3755 {
3756 auto last_token = get_token_string();
3757 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::bson, "string length must be at least 1, is " + std::to_string(len), "string")));
3758 }
3759
3760 return get_string(input_format_t::bson, len - static_cast<NumberType>(1), result) and get() != std::char_traits<char>::eof();
3761 }
3762
3773 bool parse_bson_element_internal(const int element_type,
3774 const std::size_t element_type_parse_position)
3775 {
3776 switch (element_type)
3777 {
3778 case 0x01: // double
3779 {
3780 double number;
3781 return get_number<double, true>(input_format_t::bson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
3782 }
3783
3784 case 0x02: // string
3785 {
3786 std::int32_t len;
3787 string_t value;
3788 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) and get_bson_string(len, value) and sax->string(value);
3789 }
3790
3791 case 0x03: // object
3792 {
3793 return parse_bson_internal();
3794 }
3795
3796 case 0x04: // array
3797 {
3798 return parse_bson_array();
3799 }
3800
3801 case 0x08: // boolean
3802 {
3803 return sax->boolean(get() != 0);
3804 }
3805
3806 case 0x0A: // null
3807 {
3808 return sax->null();
3809 }
3810
3811 case 0x10: // int32
3812 {
3813 std::int32_t value;
3814 return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
3815 }
3816
3817 case 0x12: // int64
3818 {
3819 std::int64_t value;
3820 return get_number<std::int64_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) and sax->number_integer(value);
3821 }
3822
3823 default: // anything else not supported (yet)
3824 {
3825 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
3826 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(element_type));
3827 return sax->parse_error(element_type_parse_position, std::string(cr.data()), parse_error::create(114, element_type_parse_position, "Unsupported BSON record type 0x" + std::string(cr.data())));
3828 }
3829 }
3830 }
3831
3844 bool parse_bson_element_list(const bool is_array)
3845 {
3846 string_t key;
3847 while (int element_type = get())
3848 {
3849 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "element list")))
3850 {
3851 return false;
3852 }
3853
3854 const std::size_t element_type_parse_position = chars_read;
3855 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_bson_cstr(key)))
3856 {
3857 return false;
3858 }
3859
3860 if (not is_array and not sax->key(key))
3861 {
3862 return false;
3863 }
3864
3865 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_internal(element_type, element_type_parse_position)))
3866 {
3867 return false;
3868 }
3869
3870 // get_bson_cstr only appends
3871 key.clear();
3872 }
3873
3874 return true;
3875 }
3876
3881 bool parse_bson_array()
3882 {
3883 std::int32_t document_size;
3884 get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
3885
3886 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
3887 {
3888 return false;
3889 }
3890
3891 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/true)))
3892 {
3893 return false;
3894 }
3895
3896 return sax->end_array();
3897 }
3898
3900 // CBOR //
3902
3910 bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char = true)
3911 {
3912 switch (get_char ? get() : current)
3913 {
3914 // EOF
3915 case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
3916 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "value");
3917
3918 // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
3919 case 0x00:
3920 case 0x01:
3921 case 0x02:
3922 case 0x03:
3923 case 0x04:
3924 case 0x05:
3925 case 0x06:
3926 case 0x07:
3927 case 0x08:
3928 case 0x09:
3929 case 0x0A:
3930 case 0x0B:
3931 case 0x0C:
3932 case 0x0D:
3933 case 0x0E:
3934 case 0x0F:
3935 case 0x10:
3936 case 0x11:
3937 case 0x12:
3938 case 0x13:
3939 case 0x14:
3940 case 0x15:
3941 case 0x16:
3942 case 0x17:
3943 return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
3944
3945 case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
3946 {
3947 std::uint8_t number;
3948 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3949 }
3950
3951 case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
3952 {
3953 std::uint16_t number;
3954 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3955 }
3956
3957 case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
3958 {
3959 std::uint32_t number;
3960 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3961 }
3962
3963 case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
3964 {
3965 std::uint64_t number;
3966 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
3967 }
3968
3969 // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
3970 case 0x20:
3971 case 0x21:
3972 case 0x22:
3973 case 0x23:
3974 case 0x24:
3975 case 0x25:
3976 case 0x26:
3977 case 0x27:
3978 case 0x28:
3979 case 0x29:
3980 case 0x2A:
3981 case 0x2B:
3982 case 0x2C:
3983 case 0x2D:
3984 case 0x2E:
3985 case 0x2F:
3986 case 0x30:
3987 case 0x31:
3988 case 0x32:
3989 case 0x33:
3990 case 0x34:
3991 case 0x35:
3992 case 0x36:
3993 case 0x37:
3994 return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
3995
3996 case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
3997 {
3998 std::uint8_t number;
3999 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4000 }
4001
4002 case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
4003 {
4004 std::uint16_t number;
4005 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4006 }
4007
4008 case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
4009 {
4010 std::uint32_t number;
4011 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
4012 }
4013
4014 case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
4015 {
4016 std::uint64_t number;
4017 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1)
4018 - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
4019 }
4020
4021 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4022 case 0x60:
4023 case 0x61:
4024 case 0x62:
4025 case 0x63:
4026 case 0x64:
4027 case 0x65:
4028 case 0x66:
4029 case 0x67:
4030 case 0x68:
4031 case 0x69:
4032 case 0x6A:
4033 case 0x6B:
4034 case 0x6C:
4035 case 0x6D:
4036 case 0x6E:
4037 case 0x6F:
4038 case 0x70:
4039 case 0x71:
4040 case 0x72:
4041 case 0x73:
4042 case 0x74:
4043 case 0x75:
4044 case 0x76:
4045 case 0x77:
4046 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4047 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4048 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4049 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4050 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4051 {
4052 string_t s;
4053 return get_cbor_string(s) and sax->string(s);
4054 }
4055
4056 // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
4057 case 0x80:
4058 case 0x81:
4059 case 0x82:
4060 case 0x83:
4061 case 0x84:
4062 case 0x85:
4063 case 0x86:
4064 case 0x87:
4065 case 0x88:
4066 case 0x89:
4067 case 0x8A:
4068 case 0x8B:
4069 case 0x8C:
4070 case 0x8D:
4071 case 0x8E:
4072 case 0x8F:
4073 case 0x90:
4074 case 0x91:
4075 case 0x92:
4076 case 0x93:
4077 case 0x94:
4078 case 0x95:
4079 case 0x96:
4080 case 0x97:
4081 return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
4082
4083 case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4084 {
4085 std::uint8_t len;
4086 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4087 }
4088
4089 case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4090 {
4091 std::uint16_t len;
4092 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4093 }
4094
4095 case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4096 {
4097 std::uint32_t len;
4098 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4099 }
4100
4101 case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4102 {
4103 std::uint64_t len;
4104 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4105 }
4106
4107 case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
4108 return get_cbor_array(std::size_t(-1));
4109
4110 // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
4111 case 0xA0:
4112 case 0xA1:
4113 case 0xA2:
4114 case 0xA3:
4115 case 0xA4:
4116 case 0xA5:
4117 case 0xA6:
4118 case 0xA7:
4119 case 0xA8:
4120 case 0xA9:
4121 case 0xAA:
4122 case 0xAB:
4123 case 0xAC:
4124 case 0xAD:
4125 case 0xAE:
4126 case 0xAF:
4127 case 0xB0:
4128 case 0xB1:
4129 case 0xB2:
4130 case 0xB3:
4131 case 0xB4:
4132 case 0xB5:
4133 case 0xB6:
4134 case 0xB7:
4135 return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu));
4136
4137 case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4138 {
4139 std::uint8_t len;
4140 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4141 }
4142
4143 case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4144 {
4145 std::uint16_t len;
4146 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4147 }
4148
4149 case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4150 {
4151 std::uint32_t len;
4152 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4153 }
4154
4155 case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4156 {
4157 std::uint64_t len;
4158 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4159 }
4160
4161 case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
4162 return get_cbor_object(std::size_t(-1));
4163
4164 case 0xF4: // false
4165 return sax->boolean(false);
4166
4167 case 0xF5: // true
4168 return sax->boolean(true);
4169
4170 case 0xF6: // null
4171 return sax->null();
4172
4173 case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
4174 {
4175 const int byte1_raw = get();
4176 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
4177 {
4178 return false;
4179 }
4180 const int byte2_raw = get();
4181 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
4182 {
4183 return false;
4184 }
4185
4186 const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
4187 const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
4188
4189 // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
4190 // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
4191 // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
4192 // still only have limited support for them. It is very
4193 // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
4194 // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
4195 // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
4196 // is shown in Fig. 3.
4197 const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte1 << 8u) + byte2);
4198 const double val = [&half]
4199 {
4200 const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
4201 const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
4202 assert(0 <= exp and exp <= 32);
4203 assert(0 <= mant and mant <= 1024);
4204 switch (exp)
4205 {
4206 case 0:
4207 return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
4208 case 31:
4209 return (mant == 0)
4210 ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
4211 : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
4212 default:
4213 return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
4214 }
4215 }();
4216 return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000u) != 0
4217 ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
4218 : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
4219 }
4220
4221 case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
4222 {
4223 float number;
4224 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
4225 }
4226
4227 case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
4228 {
4229 double number;
4230 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
4231 }
4232
4233 default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
4234 {
4235 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4236 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
4237 }
4238 }
4239 }
4240
4252 bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result)
4253 {
4254 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "string")))
4255 {
4256 return false;
4257 }
4258
4259 switch (current)
4260 {
4261 // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
4262 case 0x60:
4263 case 0x61:
4264 case 0x62:
4265 case 0x63:
4266 case 0x64:
4267 case 0x65:
4268 case 0x66:
4269 case 0x67:
4270 case 0x68:
4271 case 0x69:
4272 case 0x6A:
4273 case 0x6B:
4274 case 0x6C:
4275 case 0x6D:
4276 case 0x6E:
4277 case 0x6F:
4278 case 0x70:
4279 case 0x71:
4280 case 0x72:
4281 case 0x73:
4282 case 0x74:
4283 case 0x75:
4284 case 0x76:
4285 case 0x77:
4286 {
4287 return get_string(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
4288 }
4289
4290 case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
4291 {
4292 std::uint8_t len;
4293 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4294 }
4295
4296 case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
4297 {
4298 std::uint16_t len;
4299 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4300 }
4301
4302 case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
4303 {
4304 std::uint32_t len;
4305 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4306 }
4307
4308 case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
4309 {
4310 std::uint64_t len;
4311 return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) and get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
4312 }
4313
4314 case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
4315 {
4316 while (get() != 0xFF)
4317 {
4318 string_t chunk;
4319 if (not get_cbor_string(chunk))
4320 {
4321 return false;
4322 }
4323 result.append(chunk);
4324 }
4325 return true;
4326 }
4327
4328 default:
4329 {
4330 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4331 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, "expected length specification (0x60-0x7B) or indefinite string type (0x7F); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4332 }
4333 }
4334 }
4335
4341 bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len)
4342 {
4343 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
4344 {
4345 return false;
4346 }
4347
4348 if (len != std::size_t(-1))
4349 {
4350 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4351 {
4352 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4353 {
4354 return false;
4355 }
4356 }
4357 }
4358 else
4359 {
4360 while (get() != 0xFF)
4361 {
4362 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal(false)))
4363 {
4364 return false;
4365 }
4366 }
4367 }
4368
4369 return sax->end_array();
4370 }
4371
4377 bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len)
4378 {
4379 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len)))
4380 {
4381 return false;
4382 }
4383
4384 string_t key;
4385 if (len != std::size_t(-1))
4386 {
4387 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4388 {
4389 get();
4390 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4391 {
4392 return false;
4393 }
4394
4395 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4396 {
4397 return false;
4398 }
4399 key.clear();
4400 }
4401 }
4402 else
4403 {
4404 while (get() != 0xFF)
4405 {
4406 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_cbor_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4407 {
4408 return false;
4409 }
4410
4411 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_cbor_internal()))
4412 {
4413 return false;
4414 }
4415 key.clear();
4416 }
4417 }
4418
4419 return sax->end_object();
4420 }

4728 {
4729 std::uint32_t len;
4730 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4731 }
4732
4733 case 0xDE: // map 16
4734 {
4735 std::uint16_t len;
4736 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4737 }
4738
4739 case 0xDF: // map 32
4740 {
4741 std::uint32_t len;
4742 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_msgpack_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len));
4743 }
4744
4745 // negative fixint
4746 case 0xE0:
4747 case 0xE1:
4748 case 0xE2:
4749 case 0xE3:
4750 case 0xE4:
4751 case 0xE5:
4752 case 0xE6:
4753 case 0xE7:
4754 case 0xE8:
4755 case 0xE9:
4756 case 0xEA:
4757 case 0xEB:
4758 case 0xEC:
4759 case 0xED:
4760 case 0xEE:
4761 case 0xEF:
4762 case 0xF0:
4763 case 0xF1:
4764 case 0xF2:
4765 case 0xF3:
4766 case 0xF4:
4767 case 0xF5:
4768 case 0xF6:
4769 case 0xF7:
4770 case 0xF8:
4771 case 0xF9:
4772 case 0xFA:
4773 case 0xFB:
4774 case 0xFC:
4775 case 0xFD:
4776 case 0xFE:
4777 case 0xFF:
4778 return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(current));
4779
4780 default: // anything else
4781 {
4782 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4783 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
4784 }
4785 }
4786 }
4787
4798 bool get_msgpack_string(string_t& result)
4799 {
4800 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::msgpack, "string")))
4801 {
4802 return false;
4803 }
4804
4805 switch (current)
4806 {
4807 // fixstr
4808 case 0xA0:
4809 case 0xA1:
4810 case 0xA2:
4811 case 0xA3:
4812 case 0xA4:
4813 case 0xA5:
4814 case 0xA6:
4815 case 0xA7:
4816 case 0xA8:
4817 case 0xA9:
4818 case 0xAA:
4819 case 0xAB:
4820 case 0xAC:
4821 case 0xAD:
4822 case 0xAE:
4823 case 0xAF:
4824 case 0xB0:
4825 case 0xB1:
4826 case 0xB2:
4827 case 0xB3:
4828 case 0xB4:
4829 case 0xB5:
4830 case 0xB6:
4831 case 0xB7:
4832 case 0xB8:
4833 case 0xB9:
4834 case 0xBA:
4835 case 0xBB:
4836 case 0xBC:
4837 case 0xBD:
4838 case 0xBE:
4839 case 0xBF:
4840 {
4841 return get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
4842 }
4843
4844 case 0xD9: // str 8
4845 {
4846 std::uint8_t len;
4847 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
4848 }
4849
4850 case 0xDA: // str 16
4851 {
4852 std::uint16_t len;
4853 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
4854 }
4855
4856 case 0xDB: // str 32
4857 {
4858 std::uint32_t len;
4859 return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) and get_string(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
4860 }
4861
4862 default:
4863 {
4864 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4865 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, "expected length specification (0xA0-0xBF, 0xD9-0xDB); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4866 }
4867 }
4868 }
4869
4874 bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len)
4875 {
4876 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(len)))
4877 {
4878 return false;
4879 }
4880
4881 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4882 {
4883 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
4884 {
4885 return false;
4886 }
4887 }
4888
4889 return sax->end_array();
4890 }
4891
4896 bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len)
4897 {
4898 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(len)))
4899 {
4900 return false;
4901 }
4902
4903 string_t key;
4904 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4905 {
4906 get();
4907 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_msgpack_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
4908 {
4909 return false;
4910 }
4911
4912 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_msgpack_internal()))
4913 {
4914 return false;
4915 }
4916 key.clear();
4917 }
4918
4919 return sax->end_object();
4920 }
4921
4923 // UBJSON //
4925
4933 bool parse_ubjson_internal(const bool get_char = true)
4934 {
4935 return get_ubjson_value(get_char ? get_ignore_noop() : current);
4936 }
4937
4952 bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true)
4953 {
4954 if (get_char)
4955 {
4956 get(); // TODO(niels): may we ignore N here?
4957 }
4958
4959 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
4960 {
4961 return false;
4962 }
4963
4964 switch (current)
4965 {
4966 case 'U':
4967 {
4968 std::uint8_t len;
4969 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4970 }
4971
4972 case 'i':
4973 {
4974 std::int8_t len;
4975 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4976 }
4977
4978 case 'I':
4979 {
4980 std::int16_t len;
4981 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4982 }
4983
4984 case 'l':
4985 {
4986 std::int32_t len;
4987 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4988 }
4989
4990 case 'L':
4991 {
4992 std::int64_t len;
4993 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, len) and get_string(input_format_t::ubjson, len, result);
4994 }
4995
4996 default:
4997 auto last_token = get_token_string();
4998 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token, "string")));
4999 }
5000 }
5001
5006 bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result)
5007 {
5008 switch (get_ignore_noop())
5009 {
5010 case 'U':
5011 {
5012 std::uint8_t number;
5013 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5014 {
5015 return false;
5016 }
5017 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5018 return true;
5019 }
5020
5021 case 'i':
5022 {
5023 std::int8_t number;
5024 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5025 {
5026 return false;
5027 }
5028 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5029 return true;
5030 }
5031
5032 case 'I':
5033 {
5034 std::int16_t number;
5035 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5036 {
5037 return false;
5038 }
5039 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5040 return true;
5041 }
5042
5043 case 'l':
5044 {
5045 std::int32_t number;
5046 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5047 {
5048 return false;
5049 }
5050 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5051 return true;
5052 }
5053
5054 case 'L':
5055 {
5056 std::int64_t number;
5057 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number)))
5058 {
5059 return false;
5060 }
5061 result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
5062 return true;
5063 }
5064
5065 default:
5066 {
5067 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5068 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
5069 }
5070 }
5071 }
5072
5083 bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, int>& result)
5084 {
5085 result.first = string_t::npos; // size
5086 result.second = 0; // type
5087
5088 get_ignore_noop();
5089
5090 if (current == '$')
5091 {
5092 result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
5093 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "type")))
5094 {
5095 return false;
5096 }
5097
5098 get_ignore_noop();
5099 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current != '#'))
5100 {
5101 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value")))
5102 {
5103 return false;
5104 }
5105 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5106 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "expected '#' after type information; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "size")));
5107 }
5108
5109 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
5110 }
5111
5112 if (current == '#')
5113 {
5114 return get_ubjson_size_value(result.first);
5115 }
5116
5117 return true;
5118 }
5119
5124 bool get_ubjson_value(const int prefix)
5125 {
5126 switch (prefix)
5127 {
5128 case std::char_traits<char>::eof(): // EOF
5129 return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "value");
5130
5131 case 'T': // true
5132 return sax->boolean(true);
5133 case 'F': // false
5134 return sax->boolean(false);
5135
5136 case 'Z': // null
5137 return sax->null();
5138
5139 case 'U':
5140 {
5141 std::uint8_t number;
5142 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_unsigned(number);
5143 }
5144
5145 case 'i':
5146 {
5147 std::int8_t number;
5148 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5149 }
5150
5151 case 'I':
5152 {
5153 std::int16_t number;
5154 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5155 }
5156
5157 case 'l':
5158 {
5159 std::int32_t number;
5160 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5161 }
5162
5163 case 'L':
5164 {
5165 std::int64_t number;
5166 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_integer(number);
5167 }
5168
5169 case 'd':
5170 {
5171 float number;
5172 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5173 }
5174
5175 case 'D':
5176 {
5177 double number;
5178 return get_number(input_format_t::ubjson, number) and sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
5179 }
5180
5181 case 'C': // char
5182 {
5183 get();
5184 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(input_format_t::ubjson, "char")))
5185 {
5186 return false;
5187 }
5188 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
5189 {
5190 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5191 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x" + last_token, "char")));
5192 }
5193 string_t s(1, static_cast<char>(current));
5194 return sax->string(s);
5195 }
5196
5197 case 'S': // string
5198 {
5199 string_t s;
5200 return get_ubjson_string(s) and sax->string(s);
5201 }
5202
5203 case '[': // array
5204 return get_ubjson_array();
5205
5206 case '{': // object
5207 return get_ubjson_object();
5208
5209 default: // anything else
5210 {
5211 auto last_token = get_token_string();
5212 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format_t::ubjson, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value")));
5213 }
5214 }
5215 }
5216
5220 bool get_ubjson_array()
5221 {
5222 std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
5223 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
5224 {
5225 return false;
5226 }
5227
5228 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
5229 {
5230 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(size_and_type.first)))
5231 {
5232 return false;
5233 }
5234
5235 if (size_and_type.second != 0)
5236 {
5237 if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
5238 {
5239 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5240 {
5241 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
5242 {
5243 return false;
5244 }
5245 }
5246 }
5247 }
5248 else
5249 {
5250 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5251 {
5252 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5253 {
5254 return false;
5255 }
5256 }
5257 }
5258 }
5259 else
5260 {
5261 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
5262 {
5263 return false;
5264 }
5265
5266 while (current != ']')
5267 {
5268 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal(false)))
5269 {
5270 return false;
5271 }
5272 get_ignore_noop();
5273 }
5274 }
5275
5276 return sax->end_array();
5277 }
5278
5282 bool get_ubjson_object()
5283 {
5284 std::pair<std::size_t, int> size_and_type;
5285 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
5286 {
5287 return false;
5288 }
5289
5290 string_t key;
5291 if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
5292 {
5293 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(size_and_type.first)))
5294 {
5295 return false;
5296 }
5297
5298 if (size_and_type.second != 0)
5299 {
5300 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5301 {
5302 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
5303 {
5304 return false;
5305 }
5306 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
5307 {
5308 return false;
5309 }
5310 key.clear();
5311 }
5312 }
5313 else
5314 {
5315 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
5316 {
5317 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key) or not sax->key(key)))
5318 {
5319 return false;
5320 }
5321 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5322 {
5323 return false;
5324 }
5325 key.clear();
5326 }
5327 }
5328 }
5329 else
5330 {
5331 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
5332 {
5333 return false;
5334 }
5335
5336 while (current != '}')
5337 {
5338 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not get_ubjson_string(key, false) or not sax->key(key)))
5339 {
5340 return false;
5341 }
5342 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not parse_ubjson_internal()))
5343 {
5344 return false;
5345 }
5346 get_ignore_noop();
5347 key.clear();
5348 }
5349 }
5350
5351 return sax->end_object();
5352 }
5353
5355 // Utility functions //
5357
5367 int get()
5368 {
5369 ++chars_read;
5370 return current = ia->get_character();
5371 }
5372
5376 int get_ignore_noop()
5377 {
5378 do
5379 {
5380 get();
5381 }
5382 while (current == 'N');
5383
5384 return current;
5385 }
5386
5387 /*
5388 @brief read a number from the input
5389
5390 @tparam NumberType the type of the number
5391 @param[in] format the current format (for diagnostics)
5392 @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
5393
5394 @return whether conversion completed
5395
5396 @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because
5397 bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
5398 (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
5399 */
5400 template<typename NumberType, bool InputIsLittleEndian = false>
5401 bool get_number(const input_format_t format, NumberType& result)
5402 {
5403 // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
5404 std::array<std::uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
5405 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
5406 {
5407 get();
5408 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "number")))
5409 {
5410 return false;
5411 }
5412
5413 // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
5414 if (is_little_endian != InputIsLittleEndian)
5415 {
5416 vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current);
5417 }
5418 else
5419 {
5420 vec[i] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5421 }
5422 }
5423
5424 // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
5425 std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
5426 return true;
5427 }
5428
5443 template<typename NumberType>
5444 bool get_string(const input_format_t format,
5445 const NumberType len,
5446 string_t& result)
5447 {
5448 bool success = true;
5449 std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(result), len, [this, &success, &format]()
5450 {
5451 get();
5452 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not unexpect_eof(format, "string")))
5453 {
5454 success = false;
5455 }
5456 return static_cast<char>(current);
5457 });
5458 return success;
5459 }
5460
5466 bool unexpect_eof(const input_format_t format, const char* context) const
5467 {
5468 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
5469 {
5470 return sax->parse_error(chars_read, "<end of file>",
5471 parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "unexpected end of input", context)));
5472 }
5473 return true;
5474 }
5475
5479 std::string get_token_string() const
5480 {
5481 std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
5482 (std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current));
5483 return std::string{cr.data()};
5484 }
5485
5492 std::string exception_message(const input_format_t format,
5493 const std::string& detail,
5494 const std::string& context) const
5495 {
5496 std::string error_msg = "syntax error while parsing ";
5497
5498 switch (format)
5499 {
5500 case input_format_t::cbor:
5501 error_msg += "CBOR";
5502 break;
5503
5504 case input_format_t::msgpack:
5505 error_msg += "MessagePack";
5506 break;
5507
5508 case input_format_t::ubjson:
5509 error_msg += "UBJSON";
5510 break;
5511
5512 case input_format_t::bson:
5513 error_msg += "BSON";
5514 break;
5515
5516 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5517 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
5518 }
5519
5520 return error_msg + " " + context + ": " + detail;
5521 }
5522
5523 private:
5525 input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
5526
5528 int current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
5529
5531 std::size_t chars_read = 0;
5532
5534 const bool is_little_endian = little_endianess();
5535
5537 json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
5538 };
5539 } // namespace detail
5540} // namespace nlohmann

5569 // lexer //
5571
5577 template<typename BasicJsonType>
5578 class lexer
5579 {
5580 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
5581 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
5582 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
5583 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
5584
5585 public:
5587 enum class token_type
5588 {
5589 uninitialized,
5590 literal_true,
5591 literal_false,
5592 literal_null,
5593 value_string,
5594 value_unsigned,
5595 value_integer,
5596 value_float,
5597 begin_array,
5598 begin_object,
5599 end_array,
5600 end_object,
5601 name_separator,
5602 value_separator,
5603 parse_error,
5604 end_of_input,
5605 literal_or_value
5606 };
5607
5609 static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
5610 {
5611 switch (t)
5612 {
5613 case token_type::uninitialized:
5614 return "<uninitialized>";
5615 case token_type::literal_true:
5616 return "true literal";
5617 case token_type::literal_false:
5618 return "false literal";
5619 case token_type::literal_null:
5620 return "null literal";
5621 case token_type::value_string:
5622 return "string literal";
5623 case lexer::token_type::value_unsigned:
5624 case lexer::token_type::value_integer:
5625 case lexer::token_type::value_float:
5626 return "number literal";
5627 case token_type::begin_array:
5628 return "'['";
5629 case token_type::begin_object:
5630 return "'{'";
5631 case token_type::end_array:
5632 return "']'";
5633 case token_type::end_object:
5634 return "'}'";
5635 case token_type::name_separator:
5636 return "':'";
5637 case token_type::value_separator:
5638 return "','";
5639 case token_type::parse_error:
5640 return "<parse error>";
5641 case token_type::end_of_input:
5642 return "end of input";
5643 case token_type::literal_or_value:
5644 return "'[', '{', or a literal";
5645 // LCOV_EXCL_START
5646 default: // catch non-enum values
5647 return "unknown token";
5648 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
5649 }
5650 }
5651
5652 explicit lexer(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter)
5653 : ia(std::move(adapter)), decimal_point_char(get_decimal_point()) {}
5654
5655 // delete because of pointer members
5656 lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
5657 lexer(lexer&&) = delete;
5658 lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
5659 lexer& operator=(lexer&&) = delete;
5660 ~lexer() = default;
5661
5662 private:
5664 // locales
5666
5668 static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
5669 {
5670 const auto loc = localeconv();
5671 assert(loc != nullptr);
5672 return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
5673 }
5674
5676 // scan functions
5678
5694 int get_codepoint()
5695 {
5696 // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
5697 assert(current == 'u');
5698 int codepoint = 0;
5699
5700 const auto factors = { 12u, 8u, 4u, 0u };
5701 for (const auto factor : factors)
5702 {
5703 get();
5704
5705 if (current >= '0' and current <= '9')
5706 {
5707 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x30u) << factor);
5708 }
5709 else if (current >= 'A' and current <= 'F')
5710 {
5711 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x37u) << factor);
5712 }
5713 else if (current >= 'a' and current <= 'f')
5714 {
5715 codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x57u) << factor);
5716 }
5717 else
5718 {
5719 return -1;
5720 }
5721 }
5722
5723 assert(0x0000 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
5724 return codepoint;
5725 }
5726
5742 bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<int> ranges)
5743 {
5744 assert(ranges.size() == 2 or ranges.size() == 4 or ranges.size() == 6);
5745 add(current);
5746
5747 for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
5748 {
5749 get();
5750 if (JSON_LIKELY(*range <= current and current <= *(++range)))
5751 {
5752 add(current);
5753 }
5754 else
5755 {
5756 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
5757 return false;
5758 }
5759 }
5760
5761 return true;
5762 }
5763
5779 token_type scan_string()
5780 {
5781 // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
5782 reset();
5783
5784 // we entered the function by reading an open quote
5785 assert(current == '\"');
5786
5787 while (true)
5788 {
5789 // get next character
5790 switch (get())
5791 {
5792 // end of file while parsing string
5793 case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
5794 {
5795 error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
5796 return token_type::parse_error;
5797 }
5798
5799 // closing quote
5800 case '\"':
5801 {
5802 return token_type::value_string;
5803 }
5804
5805 // escapes
5806 case '\\':
5807 {
5808 switch (get())
5809 {
5810 // quotation mark
5811 case '\"':
5812 add('\"');
5813 break;
5814 // reverse solidus
5815 case '\\':
5816 add('\\');
5817 break;
5818 // solidus
5819 case '/':
5820 add('/');
5821 break;
5822 // backspace
5823 case 'b':
5824 add('\b');
5825 break;
5826 // form feed
5827 case 'f':
5828 add('\f');
5829 break;
5830 // line feed
5831 case 'n':
5832 add('\n');
5833 break;
5834 // carriage return
5835 case 'r':
5836 add('\r');
5837 break;
5838 // tab
5839 case 't':
5840 add('\t');
5841 break;
5842
5843 // unicode escapes
5844 case 'u':
5845 {
5846 const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
5847 int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
5848
5849 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
5850 {
5851 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
5852 return token_type::parse_error;
5853 }
5854
5855 // check if code point is a high surrogate
5856 if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
5857 {
5858 // expect next \uxxxx entry
5859 if (JSON_LIKELY(get() == '\\' and get() == 'u'))
5860 {
5861 const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
5862
5863 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
5864 {
5865 error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
5866 return token_type::parse_error;
5867 }
5868
5869 // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
5870 if (JSON_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 and codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
5871 {
5872 // overwrite codepoint
5873 codepoint = static_cast<int>(
5874 // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
5875 (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint1) << 10u)
5876 // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
5877 + static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint2)
5878 // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
5879 // in the result so we have to subtract with:
5880 // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
5881 - 0x35FDC00u);
5882 }
5883 else
5884 {
5885 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
5886 return token_type::parse_error;
5887 }
5888 }
5889 else
5890 {
5891 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
5892 return token_type::parse_error;
5893 }
5894 }
5895 else
5896 {
5897 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 and codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
5898 {
5899 error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
5900 return token_type::parse_error;
5901 }
5902 }
5903
5904 // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
5905 assert(0x00 <= codepoint and codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
5906
5907 // translate codepoint into bytes
5908 if (codepoint < 0x80)
5909 {
5910 // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
5911 add(codepoint);
5912 }
5913 else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
5914 {
5915 // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
5916 add(static_cast<int>(0xC0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u)));
5917 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5918 }
5919 else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
5920 {
5921 // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5922 add(static_cast<int>(0xE0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u)));
5923 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
5924 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5925 }
5926 else
5927 {
5928 // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
5929 add(static_cast<int>(0xF0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 18u)));
5930 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu)));
5931 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
5932 add(static_cast<int>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
5933 }
5934
5935 break;
5936 }
5937
5938 // other characters after escape
5939 default:
5940 error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
5941 return token_type::parse_error;
5942 }
5943
5944 break;
5945 }
5946
5947 // invalid control characters
5948 case 0x00:
5949 {
5950 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0000 (NUL) must be escaped to \\u0000";
5951 return token_type::parse_error;
5952 }
5953
5954 case 0x01:
5955 {
5956 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0001 (SOH) must be escaped to \\u0001";
5957 return token_type::parse_error;
5958 }
5959
5960 case 0x02:
5961 {
5962 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0002 (STX) must be escaped to \\u0002";
5963 return token_type::parse_error;
5964 }
5965
5966 case 0x03:
5967 {
5968 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0003 (ETX) must be escaped to \\u0003";
5969 return token_type::parse_error;
5970 }
5971
5972 case 0x04:
5973 {
5974 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0004 (EOT) must be escaped to \\u0004";
5975 return token_type::parse_error;
5976 }
5977
5978 case 0x05:
5979 {
5980 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0005 (ENQ) must be escaped to \\u0005";
5981 return token_type::parse_error;
5982 }
5983
5984 case 0x06:
5985 {
5986 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0006 (ACK) must be escaped to \\u0006";
5987 return token_type::parse_error;
5988 }
5989
5990 case 0x07:
5991 {
5992 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0007 (BEL) must be escaped to \\u0007";
5993 return token_type::parse_error;
5994 }
5995
5996 case 0x08:
5997 {
5998 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0008 (BS) must be escaped to \\u0008 or \\b";
5999 return token_type::parse_error;
6000 }

6002 case 0x09:
6003 {
6004 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0009 (HT) must be escaped to \\u0009 or \\t";
6005 return token_type::parse_error;
6006 }
6007
6008 case 0x0A:
6009 {
6010 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000A (LF) must be escaped to \\u000A or \\n";
6011 return token_type::parse_error;
6012 }
6013

6015 {
6016 error_message = "invalid string: control character U+000B (VT) must be escaped to \\u000B";
6017 return token_type::parse_error;
6018 }

6020 case 0x0C:

6280 case 0xE0:

6283 {

6285 }

6300 case 0xEA:

6305 {

6307 {
6308 return token_type::parse_error;
6309 }
6310 break;
6311 }

6314 case 0xED:
6315 {
6316 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6317 {
6318 return token_type::parse_error;
6319 }
6320 break;
6321 }
6322

6324 case 0xF0:
6325 {
6326 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6327 {
6328 return token_type::parse_error;
6329 }
6330 break;
6331 }
6332
6333 // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
6334 case 0xF1:
6335 case 0xF2:
6336 case 0xF3:
6337 {
6338 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6339 {
6340 return token_type::parse_error;
6341 }
6342 break;
6343 }
6344
6345 // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
6346 case 0xF4:
6347 {
6348 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not (next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
6349 {
6350 return token_type::parse_error;
6351 }
6352 break;
6353 }
6354
6355 // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
6356 default:
6357 {
6358 error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6359 return token_type::parse_error;
6360 }
6361 }
6362 }
6363 }

6365 static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6366 {
6367 f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
6368 }
6369
6370 static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6371 {
6372 f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
6373 }
6374
6375 static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
6376 {
6377 f = std::strtold(str, endptr);

6379
6420 token_type scan_number() // lgtm [cpp/use-of-goto]
6421 {
6422 // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
6423 reset();
6424
6425 // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
6426 // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
6427 token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
6428
6429 // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
6430 switch (current)
6431 {
6432 case '-':
6433 {
6434 add(current);
6435 goto scan_number_minus;
6436 }
6437
6438 case '0':
6439 {
6440 add(current);
6441 goto scan_number_zero;
6442 }
6443
6444 case '1':
6445 case '2':
6446 case '3':
6447 case '4':
6448 case '5':
6449 case '6':
6450 case '7':
6451 case '8':
6452 case '9':
6453 {
6454 add(current);
6455 goto scan_number_any1;
6456 }
6457
6458 // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
6459 default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6460 assert(false); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
6461 }
6462
6463 scan_number_minus:
6464 // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
6465 number_type = token_type::value_integer;
6466 switch (get())
6467 {
6468 case '0':
6469 {
6470 add(current);
6471 goto scan_number_zero;
6472 }
6473
6474 case '1':
6475 case '2':
6476 case '3':
6477 case '4':
6478 case '5':
6479 case '6':
6480 case '7':
6481 case '8':
6482 case '9':
6483 {
6484 add(current);
6485 goto scan_number_any1;
6486 }
6487
6488 default:
6489 {
6490 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
6491 return token_type::parse_error;
6492 }
6493 }
6494
6495 scan_number_zero:
6496 // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6497 switch (get())
6498 {
6499 case '.':
6500 {
6501 add(decimal_point_char);
6502 goto scan_number_decimal1;
6503 }
6504
6505 case 'e':
6506 case 'E':
6507 {
6508 add(current);
6509 goto scan_number_exponent;
6510 }
6511
6512 default:
6513 goto scan_number_done;
6514 }
6515
6516 scan_number_any1:
6517 // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
6518 switch (get())
6519 {
6520 case '0':
6521 case '1':
6522 case '2':
6523 case '3':
6524 case '4':
6525 case '5':
6526 case '6':
6527 case '7':
6528 case '8':
6529 case '9':
6530 {
6531 add(current);
6532 goto scan_number_any1;
6533 }
6534
6535 case '.':
6536 {
6537 add(decimal_point_char);
6538 goto scan_number_decimal1;
6539 }
6540
6541 case 'e':
6542 case 'E':
6543 {
6544 add(current);
6545 goto scan_number_exponent;
6546 }
6547
6548 default:
6549 goto scan_number_done;
6550 }
6551
6552 scan_number_decimal1:
6553 // state: we just parsed a decimal point
6554 number_type = token_type::value_float;
6555 switch (get())
6556 {
6557 case '0':
6558 case '1':
6559 case '2':
6560 case '3':
6561 case '4':
6562 case '5':
6563 case '6':
6564 case '7':
6565 case '8':
6566 case '9':
6567 {
6568 add(current);
6569 goto scan_number_decimal2;
6570 }
6571
6572 default:
6573 {
6574 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
6575 return token_type::parse_error;
6576 }
6577 }
6578
6579 scan_number_decimal2:
6580 // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
6581 switch (get())
6582 {
6583 case '0':
6584 case '1':
6585 case '2':
6586 case '3':
6587 case '4':
6588 case '5':
6589 case '6':
6590 case '7':
6591 case '8':
6592 case '9':
6593 {
6594 add(current);
6595 goto scan_number_decimal2;
6596 }
6597
6598 case 'e':
6599 case 'E':
6600 {
6601 add(current);
6602 goto scan_number_exponent;
6603 }
6604
6605 default:
6606 goto scan_number_done;
6607 }
6608
6609 scan_number_exponent:
6610 // we just parsed an exponent
6611 number_type = token_type::value_float;
6612 switch (get())
6613 {
6614 case '+':
6615 case '-':
6616 {
6617 add(current);
6618 goto scan_number_sign;
6619 }
6620
6621 case '0':
6622 case '1':
6623 case '2':
6624 case '3':
6625 case '4':
6626 case '5':
6627 case '6':
6628 case '7':
6629 case '8':
6630 case '9':
6631 {
6632 add(current);
6633 goto scan_number_any2;
6634 }
6635
6636 default:
6637 {
6638 error_message =
6639 "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
6640 return token_type::parse_error;
6641 }
6642 }
6643
6644 scan_number_sign:
6645 // we just parsed an exponent sign
6646 switch (get())
6647 {
6648 case '0':
6649 case '1':
6650 case '2':
6651 case '3':
6652 case '4':
6653 case '5':
6654 case '6':
6655 case '7':
6656 case '8':
6657 case '9':
6658 {
6659 add(current);
6660 goto scan_number_any2;
6661 }
6662
6663 default:
6664 {
6665 error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
6666 return token_type::parse_error;
6667 }
6668 }
6669
6670 scan_number_any2:
6671 // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
6672 switch (get())
6673 {
6674 case '0':
6675 case '1':
6676 case '2':
6677 case '3':
6678 case '4':
6679 case '5':
6680 case '6':
6681 case '7':
6682 case '8':
6683 case '9':
6684 {
6685 add(current);
6686 goto scan_number_any2;
6687 }
6688
6689 default:
6690 goto scan_number_done;
6691 }
6692
6693 scan_number_done:
6694 // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
6695 // we are done scanning a number)
6696 unget();
6697
6698 char* endptr = nullptr;
6699 errno = 0;
6700
6701 // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
6702 if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
6703 {
6704 const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
6705
6706 // we checked the number format before
6707 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6708
6709 if (errno == 0)
6710 {
6711 value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
6712 if (value_unsigned == x)
6713 {
6714 return token_type::value_unsigned;
6715 }
6716 }
6717 }
6718 else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
6719 {
6720 const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
6721
6722 // we checked the number format before
6723 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6724
6725 if (errno == 0)
6726 {
6727 value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
6728 if (value_integer == x)
6729 {
6730 return token_type::value_integer;
6731 }
6732 }
6733 }
6734
6735 // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
6736 // integer conversion above failed
6737 strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
6738
6739 // we checked the number format before
6740 assert(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
6741
6742 return token_type::value_float;
6743 }
6744
6750 token_type scan_literal(const char* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
6751 token_type return_type)
6752 {
6753 assert(current == literal_text[0]);
6754 for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
6755 {
6756 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get() != literal_text[i]))
6757 {
6758 error_message = "invalid literal";
6759 return token_type::parse_error;
6760 }
6761 }
6762 return return_type;
6763 }
6764
6766 // input management
6768
6770 void reset() noexcept
6771 {
6772 token_buffer.clear();
6773 token_string.clear();
6774 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
6775 }
6776
6777 /*
6778 @brief get next character from the input
6779
6780 This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
6781 not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
6782 `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
6783 for use in error messages.
6784
6785 @return character read from the input
6786 */
6787 std::char_traits<char>::int_type get()
6788 {
6789 ++position.chars_read_total;
6790 ++position.chars_read_current_line;
6791
6792 if (next_unget)
6793 {
6794 // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
6795 next_unget = false;
6796 }
6797 else
6798 {
6799 current = ia->get_character();
6800 }
6801
6802 if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6803 {
6804 token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(current));
6805 }
6806
6807 if (current == '\n')
6808 {
6809 ++position.lines_read;
6810 position.chars_read_current_line = 0;
6811 }
6812
6813 return current;
6814 }
6815
6824 void unget()
6825 {
6826 next_unget = true;
6827
6828 --position.chars_read_total;
6829
6830 // in case we "unget" a newline, we have to also decrement the lines_read
6831 if (position.chars_read_current_line == 0)
6832 {
6833 if (position.lines_read > 0)
6834 {
6835 --position.lines_read;
6836 }
6837 }
6838 else
6839 {
6840 --position.chars_read_current_line;
6841 }
6842
6843 if (JSON_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char>::eof()))
6844 {
6845 assert(not token_string.empty());
6846 token_string.pop_back();
6847 }
6848 }
6849
6851 void add(int c)
6852 {
6853 token_buffer.push_back(std::char_traits<char>::to_char_type(c));
6854 }
6855
6856 public:
6858 // value getters
6860
6862 constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
6863 {
6864 return value_integer;
6865 }
6866
6868 constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
6869 {
6870 return value_unsigned;
6871 }
6872
6874 constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
6875 {
6876 return value_float;
6877 }
6878
6880 string_t& get_string()
6881 {
6882 return token_buffer;
6883 }
6884
6886 // diagnostics
6888
6890 constexpr position_t get_position() const noexcept
6891 {
6892 return position;
6893 }
6894
6898 std::string get_token_string() const
6899 {
6900 // escape control characters
6901 std::string result;
6902 for (const auto c : token_string)
6903 {
6904 if ('\x00' <= c and c <= '\x1F')
6905 {
6906 // escape control characters
6907 std::array<char, 9> cs{{}};
6908 (std::snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c));
6909 result += cs.data();
6910 }
6911 else
6912 {
6913 // add character as is
6914 result.push_back(c);
6915 }
6916 }
6917
6918 return result;
6919 }
6920
6922 constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
6923 {
6924 return error_message;
6925 }
6926
6928 // actual scanner
6930
6935 bool skip_bom()
6936 {
6937 if (get() == 0xEF)
6938 {
6939 // check if we completely parse the BOM
6940 return get() == 0xBB and get() == 0xBF;
6941 }
6942
6943 // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
6944 // process is later
6945 unget();
6946 return true;
6947 }
6948
6949 token_type scan()
6950 {
6951 // initially, skip the BOM
6952 if (position.chars_read_total == 0 and not skip_bom())
6953 {
6954 error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
6955 return token_type::parse_error;
6956 }
6957
6958 // read next character and ignore whitespace
6959 do
6960 {
6961 get();
6962 }
6963 while (current == ' ' or current == '\t' or current == '\n' or current == '\r');
6964
6965 switch (current)
6966 {
6967 // structural characters
6968 case '[':
6969 return token_type::begin_array;
6970 case ']':
6971 return token_type::end_array;
6972 case '{':
6973 return token_type::begin_object;
6974 case '}':
6975 return token_type::end_object;
6976 case ':':
6977 return token_type::name_separator;
6978 case ',':
6979 return token_type::value_separator;
6980
6981 // literals
6982 case 't':
6983 return scan_literal("true", 4, token_type::literal_true);
6984 case 'f':
6985 return scan_literal("false", 5, token_type::literal_false);
6986 case 'n':
6987 return scan_literal("null", 4, token_type::literal_null);
6988
6989 // string
6990 case '\"':
6991 return scan_string();
6992
6993 // number
6994 case '-':
6995 case '0':
6996 case '1':
6997 case '2':
6998 case '3':
6999 case '4':
7000 case '5':
7001 case '6':
7002 case '7':
7003 case '8':
7004 case '9':
7005 return scan_number();
7006
7007 // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
7008 // string literals)
7009 case '\0':
7010 case std::char_traits<char>::eof():
7011 return token_type::end_of_input;
7012
7013 // error
7014 default:
7015 error_message = "invalid literal";
7016 return token_type::parse_error;
7017 }
7018 }
7019
7020 private:
7022 detail::input_adapter_t ia = nullptr;
7023
7025 std::char_traits<char>::int_type current = std::char_traits<char>::eof();
7026
7028 bool next_unget = false;
7029
7031 position_t position {};
7032
7034 std::vector<char> token_string {};
7035
7037 string_t token_buffer {};
7038
7040 const char* error_message = "";
7041
7042 // number values
7043 number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
7044 number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
7045 number_float_t value_float = 0;
7046
7048 const char decimal_point_char = '.';
7049 };
7050 } // namespace detail
7051} // namespace nlohmann

7056#include <cassert> // assert
7057#include <cmath> // isfinite
7058#include <cstdint> // uint8_t
7059#include <functional> // function
7060#include <string> // string
7061#include <utility> // move
7062#include <vector> // vector
7063
7064// #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
7065
7066// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/input_adapters.hpp>
7067
7068// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/json_sax.hpp>
7069
7070// #include <nlohmann/detail/input/lexer.hpp>
7071
7072// #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
7073
7074// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/is_sax.hpp>
7075
7076// #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
7077
7078
7079namespace nlohmann
7080{
7081 namespace detail
7082 {
7084 // parser //
7086
7092 template<typename BasicJsonType>
7093 class parser
7094 {
7095 using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
7096 using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
7097 using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
7098 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
7099 using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType>;
7100 using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
7101
7102 public:
7103 enum class parse_event_t : uint8_t
7104 {
7106 object_start,
7108 object_end,
7110 array_start,
7112 array_end,
7114 key,
7116 value
7117 };
7118
7119 using parser_callback_t =
7120 std::function<bool(int depth, parse_event_t event, BasicJsonType& parsed)>;
7121
7123 explicit parser(detail::input_adapter_t&& adapter,
7124 const parser_callback_t cb = nullptr,
7125 const bool allow_exceptions_ = true)
7126 : callback(cb), m_lexer(std::move(adapter)), allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
7127 {
7128 // read first token
7129 get_token();
7130 }
7131
7142 void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
7143 {
7144 if (callback)
7145 {
7146 json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
7147 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7148 result.assert_invariant();
7149
7150 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7151 if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7152 {
7153 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7154 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7155 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7156 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7157 }
7158
7159 // in case of an error, return discarded value
7160 if (sdp.is_errored())
7161 {
7162 result = value_t::discarded;
7163 return;
7164 }
7165
7166 // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
7167 // function
7168 if (result.is_discarded())
7169 {
7170 result = nullptr;
7171 }
7172 }
7173 else
7174 {
7175 json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
7176 sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
7177 result.assert_invariant();
7178
7179 // in strict mode, input must be completely read
7180 if (strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7181 {
7182 sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7183 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7184 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7185 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7186 }
7187
7188 // in case of an error, return discarded value
7189 if (sdp.is_errored())
7190 {
7191 result = value_t::discarded;
7192 return;
7193 }
7194 }
7195 }
7196
7203 bool accept(const bool strict = true)
7204 {
7205 json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
7206 return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
7207 }
7208
7209 template <typename SAX>
7210 bool sax_parse(SAX* sax, const bool strict = true)
7211 {
7212 (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
7213 const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
7214
7215 // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
7216 if (result and strict and (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
7217 {
7218 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7219 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7220 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7221 exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value")));
7222 }
7223
7224 return result;
7225 }
7226
7227 private:
7228 template <typename SAX>
7229 bool sax_parse_internal(SAX* sax)
7230 {
7231 // stack to remember the hierarchy of structured values we are parsing
7232 // true = array; false = object
7233 std::vector<bool> states;
7234 // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
7235 bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
7236
7237 while (true)
7238 {
7239 if (not skip_to_state_evaluation)
7240 {
7241 // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
7242 switch (last_token)
7243 {
7244 case token_type::begin_object:
7245 {
7246 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_object(std::size_t(-1))))
7247 {
7248 return false;
7249 }
7250
7251 // closing } -> we are done
7252 if (get_token() == token_type::end_object)
7253 {
7254 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
7255 {
7256 return false;
7257 }
7258 break;
7259 }
7260
7261 // parse key
7262 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string))
7263 {
7264 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7265 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7266 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7267 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
7268 }
7269 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
7270 {
7271 return false;
7272 }
7273
7274 // parse separator (:)
7275 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
7276 {
7277 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7278 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7279 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7280 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
7281 }
7282
7283 // remember we are now inside an object
7284 states.push_back(false);
7285
7286 // parse values
7287 get_token();
7288 continue;
7289 }
7290
7291 case token_type::begin_array:
7292 {
7293 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->start_array(std::size_t(-1))))
7294 {
7295 return false;
7296 }
7297
7298 // closing ] -> we are done
7299 if (get_token() == token_type::end_array)
7300 {
7301 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
7302 {
7303 return false;
7304 }
7305 break;
7306 }
7307
7308 // remember we are now inside an array
7309 states.push_back(true);
7310
7311 // parse values (no need to call get_token)
7312 continue;
7313 }
7314
7315 case token_type::value_float:
7316 {
7317 const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
7318
7319 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not std::isfinite(res)))
7320 {
7321 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7322 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7323 out_of_range::create(406, "number overflow parsing '" + m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'"));
7324 }
7325
7326 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string())))
7327 {
7328 return false;
7329 }
7330
7331 break;
7332 }
7333
7334 case token_type::literal_false:
7335 {
7336 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(false)))
7337 {
7338 return false;
7339 }
7340 break;
7341 }
7342
7343 case token_type::literal_null:
7344 {
7345 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->null()))
7346 {
7347 return false;
7348 }
7349 break;
7350 }
7351
7352 case token_type::literal_true:
7353 {
7354 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->boolean(true)))
7355 {
7356 return false;
7357 }
7358 break;
7359 }
7360
7361 case token_type::value_integer:
7362 {
7363 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer())))
7364 {
7365 return false;
7366 }
7367 break;
7368 }
7369
7370 case token_type::value_string:
7371 {
7372 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->string(m_lexer.get_string())))
7373 {
7374 return false;
7375 }
7376 break;
7377 }
7378
7379 case token_type::value_unsigned:
7380 {
7381 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned())))
7382 {
7383 return false;
7384 }
7385 break;
7386 }
7387
7388 case token_type::parse_error:
7389 {
7390 // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
7391 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7392 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7393 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7394 exception_message(token_type::uninitialized, "value")));
7395 }
7396
7397 default: // the last token was unexpected
7398 {
7399 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7400 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7401 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7402 exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value, "value")));
7403 }
7404 }
7405 }
7406 else
7407 {
7408 skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
7409 }
7410
7411 // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
7412 if (states.empty())
7413 {
7414 // empty stack: we reached the end of the hierarchy: done
7415 return true;
7416 }
7417
7418 if (states.back()) // array
7419 {
7420 // comma -> next value
7421 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
7422 {
7423 // parse a new value
7424 get_token();
7425 continue;
7426 }
7427
7428 // closing ]
7429 if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array))
7430 {
7431 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_array()))
7432 {
7433 return false;
7434 }
7435
7436 // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
7437 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
7438 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
7439 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
7440 assert(not states.empty());
7441 states.pop_back();
7442 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
7443 continue;
7444 }
7445
7446 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7447 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7448 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7449 exception_message(token_type::end_array, "array")));
7450 }
7451 else // object
7452 {
7453 // comma -> next value
7454 if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
7455 {
7456 // parse key
7457 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string))
7458 {
7459 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7460 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7461 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7462 exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key")));
7463 }
7464
7465 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
7466 {
7467 return false;
7468 }
7469
7470 // parse separator (:)
7471 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
7472 {
7473 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7474 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7475 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7476 exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator")));
7477 }
7478
7479 // parse values
7480 get_token();
7481 continue;
7482 }
7483
7484 // closing }
7485 if (JSON_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object))
7486 {
7487 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not sax->end_object()))
7488 {
7489 return false;
7490 }
7491
7492 // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
7493 // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
7494 // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
7495 // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
7496 assert(not states.empty());
7497 states.pop_back();
7498 skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
7499 continue;
7500 }
7501
7502 return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
7503 m_lexer.get_token_string(),
7504 parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
7505 exception_message(token_type::end_object, "object")));
7506 }
7507 }
7508 }
7509
7511 token_type get_token()
7512 {
7513 return last_token = m_lexer.scan();
7514 }
7515
7516 std::string exception_message(const token_type expected, const std::string& context)
7517 {
7518 std::string error_msg = "syntax error ";
7519
7520 if (not context.empty())
7521 {
7522 error_msg += "while parsing " + context + " ";
7523 }
7524
7525 error_msg += "- ";
7526
7527 if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
7528 {
7529 error_msg += std::string(m_lexer.get_error_message()) + "; last read: '" +
7530 m_lexer.get_token_string() + "'";
7531 }
7532 else
7533 {
7534 error_msg += "unexpected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
7535 }
7536
7537 if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
7538 {
7539 error_msg += "; expected " + std::string(lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
7540 }
7541
7542 return error_msg;
7543 }
7544
7545 private:
7547 const parser_callback_t callback = nullptr;
7549 token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
7551 lexer_t m_lexer;
7553 const bool allow_exceptions = true;
7554 };
7555 } // namespace detail
7556} // namespace nlohmann
7557
7558// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
7559
7560
7561// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
7562
7563
7564#include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
7565#include <limits> // numeric_limits
7566
7567namespace nlohmann
7568{
7569 namespace detail
7570 {
7571 /*
7572 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
7573
7574 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
7575 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
7576 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
7577 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
7578 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
7579 */
7580 class primitive_iterator_t
7581 {
7582 private:
7583 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
7584 static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
7585 static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
7586
7588 difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
7589
7590 public:
7591 constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
7592 {
7593 return m_it;
7594 }
7595
7597 void set_begin() noexcept
7598 {
7599 m_it = begin_value;
7600 }
7601
7603 void set_end() noexcept
7604 {
7605 m_it = end_value;
7606 }
7607
7609 constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
7610 {
7611 return m_it == begin_value;
7612 }
7613
7615 constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
7616 {
7617 return m_it == end_value;
7618 }
7619
7620 friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7621 {
7622 return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
7623 }
7624
7625 friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7626 {
7627 return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
7628 }
7629
7630 primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
7631 {
7632 auto result = *this;
7633 result += n;
7634 return result;
7635 }
7636
7637 friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
7638 {
7639 return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
7640 }
7641
7642 primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
7643 {
7644 ++m_it;
7645 return *this;
7646 }
7647
7648 primitive_iterator_t const operator++(int) noexcept
7649 {
7650 auto result = *this;
7651 ++m_it;
7652 return result;
7653 }
7654
7655 primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
7656 {
7657 --m_it;
7658 return *this;
7659 }
7660
7661 primitive_iterator_t const operator--(int) noexcept
7662 {
7663 auto result = *this;
7664 --m_it;
7665 return result;
7666 }
7667
7668 primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
7669 {
7670 m_it += n;
7671 return *this;
7672 }
7673
7674 primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
7675 {
7676 m_it -= n;
7677 return *this;
7678 }
7679 };
7680 } // namespace detail
7681} // namespace nlohmann
7682
7683
7684namespace nlohmann
7685{
7686 namespace detail
7687 {
7694 template<typename BasicJsonType> struct internal_iterator
7695 {
7697 typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator {};
7699 typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator {};
7701 primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator {};
7702 };
7703 } // namespace detail
7704} // namespace nlohmann

7709#include <ciso646> // not
7710#include <iterator> // iterator, random_access_iterator_tag, bidirectional_iterator_tag, advance, next
7711#include <type_traits> // conditional, is_const, remove_const
7712
7713// #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
7714
7715// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
7716
7717// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
7718
7719// #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
7720
7721// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/cpp_future.hpp>

7723// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>

7728namespace nlohmann
