7730 namespace detail
7731 {
7732 // forward declare, to be able to friend it later on
7733 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy;
7734 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value;
7735
7752 template<typename BasicJsonType>
7753 class iter_impl
7754 {
7756 friend iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
7757 friend BasicJsonType;
7758 friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
7759 friend iteration_proxy_value<iter_impl>;
7760
7761 using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
7762 using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
7763 // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
7764 static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
7765 "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
7766
7767 public:
7768
7774 using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
7775
7777 using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
7779 using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
7781 using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
7782 typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
7783 typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
7785 using reference =
7786 typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
7787 typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
7788 typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
7789
7791 iter_impl() = default;
7792
7799 explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
7800 {
7801 assert(m_object != nullptr);
7802
7803 switch (m_object->m_type)
7804 {
7805 case value_t::object:
7806 {
7807 m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
7808 break;
7809 }
7810
7811 case value_t::array:
7812 {
7813 m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
7814 break;
7815 }
7816
7817 default:
7818 {
7819 m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
7820 break;
7821 }
7822 }
7823 }
7824
7839 iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
7840 : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it) {}
7841
7848 iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
7849 {
7850 m_object = other.m_object;
7851 m_it = other.m_it;
7852 return *this;
7853 }
7854
7855 private:
7860 void set_begin() noexcept
7861 {
7862 assert(m_object != nullptr);
7863
7864 switch (m_object->m_type)
7865 {
7866 case value_t::object:
7867 {
7868 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
7869 break;
7870 }
7871
7872 case value_t::array:
7873 {
7874 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
7875 break;
7876 }
7877
7878 case value_t::null:
7879 {
7880 // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
7881 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
7882 break;
7883 }
7884
7885 default:
7886 {
7887 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
7888 break;
7889 }
7890 }
7891 }
7892
7897 void set_end() noexcept
7898 {
7899 assert(m_object != nullptr);
7900
7901 switch (m_object->m_type)
7902 {
7903 case value_t::object:
7904 {
7905 m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
7906 break;
7907 }
7908
7909 case value_t::array:
7910 {
7911 m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
7912 break;
7913 }
7914
7915 default:
7916 {
7917 m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
7918 break;
7919 }
7920 }
7921 }
7922
7923 public:
7928 reference operator*() const
7929 {
7930 assert(m_object != nullptr);
7931
7932 switch (m_object->m_type)
7933 {
7934 case value_t::object:
7935 {
7936 assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
7937 return m_it.object_iterator->second;
7938 }
7939
7940 case value_t::array:
7941 {
7942 assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
7943 return *m_it.array_iterator;
7944 }
7945
7946 case value_t::null:
7947 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7948
7949 default:
7950 {
7951 if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
7952 {
7953 return *m_object;
7954 }
7955
7956 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7957 }
7958 }
7959 }
7960
7965 pointer operator->() const
7966 {
7967 assert(m_object != nullptr);
7968
7969 switch (m_object->m_type)
7970 {
7971 case value_t::object:
7972 {
7973 assert(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
7974 return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
7975 }
7976
7977 case value_t::array:
7978 {
7979 assert(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
7980 return &*m_it.array_iterator;
7981 }
7982
7983 default:
7984 {
7985 if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
7986 {
7987 return m_object;
7988 }
7989
7990 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
7991 }
7992 }
7993 }
7994
7999 iter_impl const operator++(int)
8000 {
8001 auto result = *this;
8002 ++(*this);
8003 return result;
8004 }
8005
8010 iter_impl& operator++()
8011 {
8012 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8013
8014 switch (m_object->m_type)
8015 {
8016 case value_t::object:
8017 {
8018 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
8019 break;
8020 }
8021
8022 case value_t::array:
8023 {
8024 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
8025 break;
8026 }
8027
8028 default:
8029 {
8030 ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
8031 break;
8032 }
8033 }
8034
8035 return *this;
8036 }
8037
8042 iter_impl const operator--(int)
8043 {
8044 auto result = *this;
8045 --(*this);
8046 return result;
8047 }
8048
8053 iter_impl& operator--()
8054 {
8055 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8056
8057 switch (m_object->m_type)
8058 {
8059 case value_t::object:
8060 {
8061 std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
8062 break;
8063 }
8064
8065 case value_t::array:
8066 {
8067 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
8068 break;
8069 }
8070
8071 default:
8072 {
8073 --m_it.primitive_iterator;
8074 break;
8075 }
8076 }
8077
8078 return *this;
8079 }
8080
8085 bool operator==(const iter_impl& other) const
8086 {
8087 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8088 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
8089 {
8090 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8091 }
8092
8093 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8094
8095 switch (m_object->m_type)
8096 {
8097 case value_t::object:
8098 return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
8099
8100 case value_t::array:
8101 return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
8102
8103 default:
8104 return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8105 }
8106 }
8107
8112 bool operator!=(const iter_impl& other) const
8113 {
8114 return not operator==(other);
8115 }
8116
8121 bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
8122 {
8123 // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
8124 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
8125 {
8126 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers"));
8127 }
8128
8129 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8130
8131 switch (m_object->m_type)
8132 {
8133 case value_t::object:
8134 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators"));
8135
8136 case value_t::array:
8137 return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
8138
8139 default:
8140 return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
8141 }
8142 }
8143
8148 bool operator<=(const iter_impl& other) const
8149 {
8150 return not other.operator < (*this);
8151 }
8152
8157 bool operator>(const iter_impl& other) const
8158 {
8159 return not operator<=(other);
8160 }
8161
8166 bool operator>=(const iter_impl& other) const
8167 {
8168 return not operator<(other);
8169 }
8170
8175 iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
8176 {
8177 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8178
8179 switch (m_object->m_type)
8180 {
8181 case value_t::object:
8182 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8183
8184 case value_t::array:
8185 {
8186 std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
8187 break;
8188 }
8189
8190 default:
8191 {
8192 m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
8193 break;
8194 }
8195 }
8196
8197 return *this;
8198 }
8199
8204 iter_impl& operator-=(difference_type i)
8205 {
8206 return operator+=(-i);
8207 }
8208
8213 iter_impl operator+(difference_type i) const
8214 {
8215 auto result = *this;
8216 result += i;
8217 return result;
8218 }
8219
8224 friend iter_impl operator+(difference_type i, const iter_impl& it)
8225 {
8226 auto result = it;
8227 result += i;
8228 return result;
8229 }
8230
8235 iter_impl operator-(difference_type i) const
8236 {
8237 auto result = *this;
8238 result -= i;
8239 return result;
8240 }
8241
8246 difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
8247 {
8248 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8249
8250 switch (m_object->m_type)
8251 {
8252 case value_t::object:
8253 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators"));
8254
8255 case value_t::array:
8256 return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
8257
8258 default:
8259 return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
8260 }
8261 }
8262
8267 reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8268 {
8269 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8270
8271 switch (m_object->m_type)
8272 {
8273 case value_t::object:
8274 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators"));
8275
8276 case value_t::array:
8277 return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
8278
8279 case value_t::null:
8280 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8281
8282 default:
8283 {
8284 if (JSON_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n))
8285 {
8286 return *m_object;
8287 }
8288
8289 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value"));
8290 }
8291 }
8292 }
8293
8298 const typename object_t::key_type& key() const
8299 {
8300 assert(m_object != nullptr);
8301
8302 if (JSON_LIKELY(m_object->is_object()))
8303 {
8304 return m_it.object_iterator->first;
8305 }
8306
8307 JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators"));
8308 }
8309
8314 reference value() const
8315 {
8316 return operator*();
8317 }
8318
8319 private:
8321 pointer m_object = nullptr;
8323 internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it {};
8324 };
8325 } // namespace detail
8326} // namespace nlohmann

8330// #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/json_reverse_iterator.hpp>

8333#include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t

8337namespace nlohmann

8339 namespace detail
8340 {
8342 // reverse_iterator //
8344
8363 template<typename Base>
8364 class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
8365 {
8366 public:
8367 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
8369 using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
8371 using reference = typename Base::reference;
8372
8374 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const typename base_iterator::iterator_type& it) noexcept
8375 : base_iterator(it) {}
8376
8378 explicit json_reverse_iterator(const base_iterator& it) noexcept : base_iterator(it) {}
8379
8381 json_reverse_iterator const operator++(int)
8382 {
8383 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
8384 }
8385
8387 json_reverse_iterator& operator++()
8388 {
8389 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++());
8390 }
8391
8393 json_reverse_iterator const operator--(int)
8394 {
8395 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
8396 }
8397
8399 json_reverse_iterator& operator--()
8400 {
8401 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--());
8402 }
8403
8405 json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i)
8406 {
8407 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
8408 }
8409
8411 json_reverse_iterator operator+(difference_type i) const
8412 {
8413 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
8414 }
8415
8417 json_reverse_iterator operator-(difference_type i) const
8418 {
8419 return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
8420 }
8421
8423 difference_type operator-(const json_reverse_iterator& other) const
8424 {
8425 return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
8426 }
8427
8429 reference operator[](difference_type n) const
8430 {
8431 return *(this->operator+(n));
8432 }
8433
8435 auto key() const -> decltype(std::declval<Base>().key())
8436 {
8437 auto it = --this->base();
8438 return it.key();
8439 }
8440
8442 reference value() const
8443 {
8444 auto it = --this->base();
8445 return it.operator * ();
8446 }
8447 };

8472 template<typename BasicJsonType>
8473 class json_pointer
8474 {
8475 // allow basic_json to access private members
8476 NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
8477 friend class basic_json;
8478
8479 public:
8501 explicit json_pointer(const std::string& s = "")
8502 : reference_tokens(split(s))
8503 {}
8504
8519 std::string to_string() const
8520 {
8521 return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(), reference_tokens.end(),
8522 std::string{},
8523 [](const std::string & a, const std::string & b)
8524 {
8525 return a + "/" + escape(b);
8526 });
8527 }
8528
8530 operator std::string() const
8531 {
8532 return to_string();
8533 }
8534
8551 json_pointer& operator/=(const json_pointer& ptr)
8552 {
8553 reference_tokens.insert(reference_tokens.end(),
8554 ptr.reference_tokens.begin(),
8555 ptr.reference_tokens.end());
8556 return *this;
8557 }
8558
8575 json_pointer& operator/=(std::string token)
8576 {
8577 push_back(std::move(token));
8578 return *this;
8579 }
8580
8597 json_pointer& operator/=(std::size_t array_index)
8598 {
8599 return *this /= std::to_string(array_index);
8600 }
8601
8617 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs,
8618 const json_pointer& rhs)
8619 {
8620 return json_pointer(lhs) /= rhs;
8621 }
8622
8638 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::string token)
8639 {
8640 return json_pointer(ptr) /= std::move(token);
8641 }
8642
8658 friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& ptr, std::size_t array_index)
8659 {
8660 return json_pointer(ptr) /= array_index;
8661 }
8662
8676 json_pointer parent_pointer() const
8677 {
8678 if (empty())
8679 {
8680 return *this;
8681 }
8682
8683 json_pointer res = *this;
8684 res.pop_back();
8685 return res;
8686 }
8687
8701 void pop_back()
8702 {
8703 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8704 {
8705 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8706 }
8707
8708 reference_tokens.pop_back();
8709 }
8710
8725 const std::string& back()
8726 {
8727 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8728 {
8729 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8730 }
8731
8732 return reference_tokens.back();
8733 }
8734
8747 void push_back(const std::string& token)
8748 {
8749 reference_tokens.push_back(token);
8750 }
8751
8753 void push_back(std::string&& token)
8754 {
8755 reference_tokens.push_back(std::move(token));
8756 }
8757
8772 bool empty() const noexcept
8773 {
8774 return reference_tokens.empty();
8775 }
8776
8777 private:
8785 static int array_index(const std::string& s)
8786 {
8787 std::size_t processed_chars = 0;
8788 const int res = std::stoi(s, &processed_chars);
8789
8790 // check if the string was completely read
8791 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(processed_chars != s.size()))
8792 {
8793 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + s + "'"));
8794 }
8795
8796 return res;
8797 }
8798
8799 json_pointer top() const
8800 {
8801 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(empty()))
8802 {
8803 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent"));
8804 }
8805
8806 json_pointer result = *this;
8807 result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
8808 return result;
8809 }
8810
8819 BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const
8820 {
8821 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8822 auto result = &j;
8823
8824 // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
8825 // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
8826 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8827 {
8828 switch (result->m_type)
8829 {
8830 case detail::value_t::null:
8831 {
8832 if (reference_token == "0")
8833 {
8834 // start a new array if reference token is 0
8835 result = &result->operator[](0);
8836 }
8837 else
8838 {
8839 // start a new object otherwise
8840 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8841 }
8842 break;
8843 }
8844
8845 case detail::value_t::object:
8846 {
8847 // create an entry in the object
8848 result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
8849 break;
8850 }
8851
8852 case detail::value_t::array:
8853 {
8854 // create an entry in the array
8855 JSON_TRY
8856 {
8857 result = &result->operator[](static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
8858 }
8859 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
8860 {
8861 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
8862 }
8863 break;
8864 }
8865
8866 /*
8867 The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
8868 token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
8869 an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
8870 single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
8871 */
8872 default:
8873 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten"));
8874 }
8875 }
8876
8877 return *result;
8878 }
8879
8899 BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
8900 {
8901 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8902 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8903 {
8904 // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
8905 if (ptr->m_type == detail::value_t::null)
8906 {
8907 // check if reference token is a number
8908 const bool nums =
8909 std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
8910 [](const char x)
8911 {
8912 return x >= '0' and x <= '9';
8913 });
8914
8915 // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
8916 *ptr = (nums or reference_token == "-")
8917 ? detail::value_t::array
8918 : detail::value_t::object;
8919 }
8920
8921 switch (ptr->m_type)
8922 {
8923 case detail::value_t::object:
8924 {
8925 // use unchecked object access
8926 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
8927 break;
8928 }
8929
8930 case detail::value_t::array:
8931 {
8932 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
8933 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
8934 {
8935 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
8936 "array index '" + reference_token +
8937 "' must not begin with '0'"));
8938 }
8939
8940 if (reference_token == "-")
8941 {
8942 // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
8943 ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
8944 }
8945 else
8946 {
8947 // convert array index to number; unchecked access
8948 JSON_TRY
8949 {
8950 ptr = &ptr->operator[](
8951 static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
8952 }
8953 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
8954 {
8955 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
8956 }
8957 }
8958 break;
8959 }
8960
8961 default:
8962 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
8963 }
8964 }
8965
8966 return *ptr;
8967 }
8968
8975 BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
8976 {
8977 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
8978 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
8979 {
8980 switch (ptr->m_type)
8981 {
8982 case detail::value_t::object:
8983 {
8984 // note: at performs range check
8985 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
8986 break;
8987 }
8988
8989 case detail::value_t::array:
8990 {
8991 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
8992 {
8993 // "-" always fails the range check
8994 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
8995 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
8996 ") is out of range"));
8997 }
8998
8999 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9000 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
9001 {
9002 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
9003 "array index '" + reference_token +
9004 "' must not begin with '0'"));
9005 }
9006
9007 // note: at performs range check
9008 JSON_TRY
9009 {
9010 ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
9011 }
9012 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
9013 {
9014 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9015 }
9016 break;
9017 }
9018
9019 default:
9020 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9021 }
9022 }
9023
9024 return *ptr;
9025 }
9026
9040 const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
9041 {
9042 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9043 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
9044 {
9045 switch (ptr->m_type)
9046 {
9047 case detail::value_t::object:
9048 {
9049 // use unchecked object access
9050 ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
9051 break;
9052 }
9053
9054 case detail::value_t::array:
9055 {
9056 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
9057 {
9058 // "-" cannot be used for const access
9059 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
9060 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
9061 ") is out of range"));
9062 }
9063
9064 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9065 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
9066 {
9067 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0,
9068 "array index '" + reference_token +
9069 "' must not begin with '0'"));
9070 }
9071
9072 // use unchecked array access
9073 JSON_TRY
9074 {
9075 ptr = &ptr->operator[](
9076 static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
9077 }
9078 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)
9079 {
9080 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, "array index '" + reference_token + "' is not a number"));
9081 }
9082 break;
9083 }
9084
9085 default:
9086 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, "unresolved reference token '" + reference_token + "'"));
9087 }
9088 }
9089
9090 return *ptr;
9091 }
9092
9099 const BasicJsonType& get_checked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
9100 {
9101 using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
9102 for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
9103 {
9104 switch (ptr->m_type)
9105 {
9106 case detail::value_t::object:
9107 {
9108 // note: at performs range check
9109 ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
9110 break;
9111 }

9114 {
9115 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
9116 {
9117 // "-" always fails the range check
9118 JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402,
9119 "array index '-' (" + std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()) +
9120 ") is out of range"));
9121 }
9122
9123 // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
9124 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1 and reference_token[0] == '0'))
9125 {

9127 "array index '" + reference_token +
9128 "' must not begin with '0'"));

9131 // note: at performs range check
9132 JSON_TRY

9134 ptr = &ptr->at(static_cast<size_type>(array_index(reference_token)));
9135 }
9136 JSON_CATCH(std::invalid_argument&)

9139 }

9150
9160 static std::vector<std::string> split(const std::string& reference_string)
9161 {
9162 std::vector<std::string> result;
9163
9164 // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
9165 if (reference_string.empty())
9166 {
9167 return result;
9168 }
9169
9170 // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
9171 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/'))
9172 {
9173 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(107, 1,
9174 "JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '" +
9175 reference_string + "'"));
9176 }
9177
9178 // extract the reference tokens:
9179 // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
9180 // - start: position after the previous slash
9181 for (
9182 // search for the first slash after the first character
9183 std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
9184 // set the beginning of the first reference token
9185 start = 1;
9186 // we can stop if start == 0 (if slash == std::string::npos)
9187 start != 0;
9188 // set the beginning of the next reference token
9189 // (will eventually be 0 if slash == std::string::npos)
9190 start = (slash == std::string::npos) ? 0 : slash + 1,
9191 // find next slash
9192 slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
9193 {
9194 // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
9195 // (start) and the last slash (slash).
9196 auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
9197
9198 // check reference tokens are properly escaped
9199 for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
9200 pos != std::string::npos;
9201 pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
9202 {
9203 assert(reference_token[pos] == '~');
9204
9205 // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
9206 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 or
9207 (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' and
9208 reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')))
9209 {
9210 JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'"));
9211 }
9212 }
9213
9214 // finally, store the reference token
9215 unescape(reference_token);
9216 result.push_back(reference_token);
9217 }
9218
9219 return result;
9220 }
9221
9235 static void replace_substring(std::string& s, const std::string& f,
9236 const std::string& t)
9237 {
9238 assert(not f.empty());
9239 for (auto pos = s.find(f); // find first occurrence of f
9240 pos != std::string::npos; // make sure f was found
9241 s.replace(pos, f.size(), t), // replace with t, and
9242 pos = s.find(f, pos + t.size())) // find next occurrence of f
9243 {}
9244 }
9245
9247 static std::string escape(std::string s)
9248 {
9249 replace_substring(s, "~", "~0");
9250 replace_substring(s, "/", "~1");
9251 return s;
9252 }
9253
9255 static void unescape(std::string& s)
9256 {
9257 replace_substring(s, "~1", "/");
9258 replace_substring(s, "~0", "~");
9259 }
9260
9268 static void flatten(const std::string& reference_string,
9269 const BasicJsonType& value,
9270 BasicJsonType& result)
9271 {
9272 switch (value.m_type)
9273 {
9274 case detail::value_t::array:
9275 {
9276 if (value.m_value.array->empty())
9277 {
9278 // flatten empty array as null
9279 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9280 }
9281 else
9282 {
9283 // iterate array and use index as reference string
9284 for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
9285 {
9286 flatten(reference_string + "/" + std::to_string(i),
9287 value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
9288 }
9289 }
9290 break;
9291 }
9292
9293 case detail::value_t::object:
9294 {
9295 if (value.m_value.object->empty())
9296 {
9297 // flatten empty object as null
9298 result[reference_string] = nullptr;
9299 }
9300 else
9301 {
9302 // iterate object and use keys as reference string
9303 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
9304 {
9305 flatten(reference_string + "/" + escape(element.first), element.second, result);
9306 }
9307 }
9308 break;
9309 }
9310
9311 default:
9312 {
9313 // add primitive value with its reference string
9314 result[reference_string] = value;
9315 break;
9316 }
9317 }
9318 }
9319
9330 static BasicJsonType
9331 unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value)
9332 {
9333 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not value.is_object()))
9334 {
9335 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened"));
9336 }
9337
9338 BasicJsonType result;
9339
9340 // iterate the JSON object values
9341 for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
9342 {
9343 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(not element.second.is_primitive()))
9344 {
9345 JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive"));
9346 }
9347
9348 // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
9349 // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
9350 // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
9351 // will then create a primitive value.
9352 json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
9353 }
9354
9355 return result;
9356 }
9357
9369 friend bool operator==(json_pointer const& lhs,
9370 json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
9371 {
9372 return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
9373 }
9374
9386 friend bool operator!=(json_pointer const& lhs,
9387 json_pointer const& rhs) noexcept
9388 {
9389 return not (lhs == rhs);
9390 }
9391
9393 std::vector<std::string> reference_tokens;
9394 };
9395} // namespace nlohmann

9403// #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>

9405
9406namespace nlohmann
9407{
9408 namespace detail
9409 {
9410 template<typename BasicJsonType>
9411 class json_ref
9412 {
9413 public:
9414 using value_type = BasicJsonType;
9415
9416 json_ref(value_type&& value)
9417 : owned_value(std::move(value)), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true)
9418 {}
9419
9420 json_ref(const value_type& value)
9421 : value_ref(const_cast<value_type*>(&value)), is_rvalue(false)
9422 {}
9423
9424 json_ref(std::initializer_list<json_ref> init)
9425 : owned_value(init), value_ref(&owned_value), is_rvalue(true)
9426 {}
9427
9428 template <
9429 class... Args,
9430 enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<value_type, Args...>::value, int> = 0 >
9431 json_ref(Args && ... args)
9432 : owned_value(std::forward<Args>(args)...), value_ref(&owned_value),
9433 is_rvalue(true) {}
9434
9435 // class should be movable only
9436 json_ref(json_ref&&) = default;
9437 json_ref(const json_ref&) = delete;
9438 json_ref& operator=(const json_ref&) = delete;
9439 json_ref& operator=(json_ref&&) = delete;
9440 ~json_ref() = default;
9441
9442 value_type moved_or_copied() const
9443 {
9444 if (is_rvalue)
9445 {
9446 return std::move(*value_ref);
9447 }
9448 return *value_ref;
9449 }
9450
9451 value_type const& operator*() const
9452 {
9453 return *static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
9454 }
9455
9456 value_type const* operator->() const
9457 {
9458 return static_cast<value_type const*>(value_ref);
9459 }
9460
9461 private:
9462 mutable value_type owned_value = nullptr;
9463 value_type* value_ref = nullptr;
9464 const bool is_rvalue;
9465 };
9466 } // namespace detail
9467} // namespace nlohmann

9502 {
9504 template<typename CharType> struct output_adapter_protocol
9505 {
9506 virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
9507 virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
9508 virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
9509 };
9510
9512 template<typename CharType>
9513 using output_adapter_t = std::shared_ptr<output_adapter_protocol<CharType>>;
9514
9516 template<typename CharType>
9517 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9518 {
9519 public:
9520 explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec) noexcept
9521 : v(vec)
9522 {}
9523
9524 void write_character(CharType c) override
9525 {
9526 v.push_back(c);
9527 }
9528
9529 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9530 {
9531 std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
9532 }
9533
9534 private:
9535 std::vector<CharType>& v;
9536 };
9537
9539 template<typename CharType>
9540 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9541 {
9542 public:
9543 explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) noexcept
9544 : stream(s)
9545 {}
9546
9547 void write_character(CharType c) override
9548 {
9549 stream.put(c);
9550 }
9551
9552 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9553 {
9554 stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
9555 }
9556
9557 private:
9558 std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
9559 };
9560
9562 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9563 class output_string_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
9564 {
9565 public:
9566 explicit output_string_adapter(StringType& s) noexcept
9567 : str(s)
9568 {}
9569
9570 void write_character(CharType c) override
9571 {
9572 str.push_back(c);
9573 }
9574
9575 void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
9576 {
9577 str.append(s, length);
9578 }
9579
9580 private:
9581 StringType& str;
9582 };
9583
9584 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
9585 class output_adapter
9586 {
9587 public:
9588 output_adapter(std::vector<CharType>& vec)
9589 : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType>>(vec)) {}
9590
9591 output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s)
9592 : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
9593
9594 output_adapter(StringType& s)
9595 : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
9596
9597 operator output_adapter_t<CharType>()
9598 {
9599 return oa;
9600 }
9601
9602 private:
9603 output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
9604 };
9605 } // namespace detail
9606} // namespace nlohmann

9609namespace nlohmann

9611 namespace detail

9614 // binary writer //
9616
9620 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
9621 class binary_writer
9622 {
9623 using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
9624
9625 public:
9631 explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(adapter)
9632 {
9633 assert(oa);
9634 }
9635
9640 void write_bson(const BasicJsonType& j)
9641 {
9642 switch (j.type())
9643 {
9644 case value_t::object:
9645 {
9646 write_bson_object(*j.m_value.object);
9647 break;
9648 }
9649
9650 default:
9651 {
9652 JSON_THROW(type_error::create(317, "to serialize to BSON, top-level type must be object, but is " + std::string(j.type_name())));
9653 }
9654 }
9655 }
9656
9660 void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
9661 {
9662 switch (j.type())
9663 {
9664 case value_t::null:
9665 {
9666 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF6));
9667 break;
9668 }
9669
9670 case value_t::boolean:
9671 {
9672 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
9673 ? to_char_type(0xF5)
9674 : to_char_type(0xF4));
9675 break;
9676 }
9677
9678 case value_t::number_integer:
9679 {
9680 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
9681 {
9682 // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
9683 // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
9684 // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
9685 if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
9686 {
9687 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9688 }
9689 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9690 {
9691 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
9692 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9693 }
9694 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9695 {
9696 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
9697 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9698 }
9699 else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9700 {
9701 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
9702 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9703 }
9704 else
9705 {
9706 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
9707 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9708 }
9709 }
9710 else
9711 {
9712 // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
9713 // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
9714 const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
9715 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
9716 {
9717 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
9718 }
9719 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9720 {
9721 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x38));
9722 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(positive_number));
9723 }
9724 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9725 {
9726 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x39));
9727 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(positive_number));
9728 }
9729 else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9730 {
9731 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3A));
9732 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(positive_number));
9733 }
9734 else
9735 {
9736 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3B));
9737 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(positive_number));
9738 }
9739 }
9740 break;
9741 }
9742
9743 case value_t::number_unsigned:
9744 {
9745 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
9746 {
9747 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9748 }
9749 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9750 {
9751 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
9752 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9753 }
9754 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9755 {
9756 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
9757 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9758 }
9759 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9760 {
9761 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
9762 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9763 }
9764 else
9765 {
9766 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
9767 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
9768 }
9769 break;
9770 }
9771
9772 case value_t::number_float:
9773 {
9774 oa->write_character(get_cbor_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
9775 write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
9776 break;
9777 }
9778
9779 case value_t::string:
9780 {
9781 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
9782 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
9783 if (N <= 0x17)
9784 {
9785 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
9786 }
9787 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9788 {
9789 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x78));
9790 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9791 }
9792 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9793 {
9794 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x79));
9795 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9796 }
9797 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9798 {
9799 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7A));
9800 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9801 }
9802 // LCOV_EXCL_START
9803 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9804 {
9805 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7B));
9806 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9807 }
9808 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9809
9810 // step 2: write the string
9811 oa->write_characters(
9812 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
9813 j.m_value.string->size());
9814 break;
9815 }
9816
9817 case value_t::array:
9818 {
9819 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
9820 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
9821 if (N <= 0x17)
9822 {
9823 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
9824 }
9825 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9826 {
9827 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x98));
9828 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9829 }
9830 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9831 {
9832 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x99));
9833 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9834 }
9835 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9836 {
9837 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9A));
9838 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9839 }
9840 // LCOV_EXCL_START
9841 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9842 {
9843 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9B));
9844 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9845 }
9846 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9847
9848 // step 2: write each element
9849 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
9850 {
9851 write_cbor(el);
9852 }
9853 break;
9854 }
9855
9856 case value_t::object:
9857 {
9858 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
9859 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
9860 if (N <= 0x17)
9861 {
9862 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
9863 }
9864 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9865 {
9866 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB8));
9867 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
9868 }
9869 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9870 {
9871 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB9));
9872 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
9873 }
9874 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9875 {
9876 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBA));
9877 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
9878 }
9879 // LCOV_EXCL_START
9880 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9881 {
9882 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBB));
9883 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
9884 }
9885 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
9886
9887 // step 2: write each element
9888 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
9889 {
9890 write_cbor(el.first);
9891 write_cbor(el.second);
9892 }
9893 break;
9894 }
9895
9896 default:
9897 break;
9898 }
9899 }
9900
9904 void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
9905 {
9906 switch (j.type())
9907 {
9908 case value_t::null: // nil
9909 {
9910 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xC0));
9911 break;
9912 }
9913
9914 case value_t::boolean: // true and false
9915 {
9916 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
9917 ? to_char_type(0xC3)
9918 : to_char_type(0xC2));
9919 break;
9920 }
9921
9922 case value_t::number_integer:
9923 {
9924 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
9925 {
9926 // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
9927 // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
9928 // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
9929 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
9930 {
9931 // positive fixnum
9932 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9933 }
9934 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
9935 {
9936 // uint 8
9937 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
9938 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9939 }
9940 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
9941 {
9942 // uint 16
9943 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
9944 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9945 }
9946 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
9947 {
9948 // uint 32
9949 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
9950 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9951 }
9952 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
9953 {
9954 // uint 64
9955 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
9956 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9957 }
9958 }
9959 else
9960 {
9961 if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
9962 {
9963 // negative fixnum
9964 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9965 }
9966 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() and
9967 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
9968 {
9969 // int 8
9970 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD0));
9971 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9972 }
9973 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() and
9974 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
9975 {
9976 // int 16
9977 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD1));
9978 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9979 }
9980 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() and
9981 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
9982 {
9983 // int 32
9984 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD2));
9985 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9986 }
9987 else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() and
9988 j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
9989 {
9990 // int 64
9991 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD3));
9992 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
9993 }
9994 }
9995 break;
9996 }
9997
9998 case value_t::number_unsigned:
9999 {
10000 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
10001 {
10002 // positive fixnum
10003 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10004 }
10005 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10006 {
10007 // uint 8
10008 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
10009 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10010 }
10011 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10012 {
10013 // uint 16
10014 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
10015 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10016 }
10017 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10018 {
10019 // uint 32
10020 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
10021 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10022 }
10023 else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
10024 {
10025 // uint 64
10026 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
10027 write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
10028 }
10029 break;
10030 }
10031
10032 case value_t::number_float:
10033 {
10034 oa->write_character(get_msgpack_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float));
10035 write_number(j.m_value.number_float);
10036 break;
10037 }
10038
10039 case value_t::string:
10040 {
10041 // step 1: write control byte and the string length
10042 const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
10043 if (N <= 31)
10044 {
10045 // fixstr
10046 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
10047 }
10048 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10049 {
10050 // str 8
10051 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD9));
10052 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
10053 }
10054 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10055 {
10056 // str 16
10057 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDA));
10058 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10059 }
10060 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10061 {
10062 // str 32
10063 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDB));
10064 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10065 }
10066
10067 // step 2: write the string
10068 oa->write_characters(
10069 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10070 j.m_value.string->size());
10071 break;
10072 }
10073
10074 case value_t::array:
10075 {
10076 // step 1: write control byte and the array size
10077 const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
10078 if (N <= 15)
10079 {
10080 // fixarray
10081 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
10082 }
10083 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10084 {
10085 // array 16
10086 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDC));
10087 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10088 }
10089 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10090 {
10091 // array 32
10092 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDD));
10093 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10094 }
10095
10096 // step 2: write each element
10097 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10098 {
10099 write_msgpack(el);
10100 }
10101 break;
10102 }
10103
10104 case value_t::object:
10105 {
10106 // step 1: write control byte and the object size
10107 const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
10108 if (N <= 15)
10109 {
10110 // fixmap
10111 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
10112 }
10113 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
10114 {
10115 // map 16
10116 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDE));
10117 write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
10118 }
10119 else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
10120 {
10121 // map 32
10122 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDF));
10123 write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
10124 }
10125
10126 // step 2: write each element
10127 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10128 {
10129 write_msgpack(el.first);
10130 write_msgpack(el.second);
10131 }
10132 break;
10133 }
10134
10135 default:
10136 break;
10137 }
10138 }
10139
10146 void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
10147 const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true)
10148 {
10149 switch (j.type())
10150 {
10151 case value_t::null:
10152 {
10153 if (add_prefix)
10154 {
10155 oa->write_character(to_char_type('Z'));
10156 }
10157 break;
10158 }
10159
10160 case value_t::boolean:
10161 {
10162 if (add_prefix)
10163 {
10164 oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
10165 ? to_char_type('T')
10166 : to_char_type('F'));
10167 }
10168 break;
10169 }
10170
10171 case value_t::number_integer:
10172 {
10173 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix);
10174 break;
10175 }
10176
10177 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10178 {
10179 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix);
10180 break;
10181 }
10182
10183 case value_t::number_float:
10184 {
10185 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix);
10186 break;
10187 }
10188
10189 case value_t::string:
10190 {
10191 if (add_prefix)
10192 {
10193 oa->write_character(to_char_type('S'));
10194 }
10195 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true);
10196 oa->write_characters(
10197 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
10198 j.m_value.string->size());
10199 break;
10200 }
10201
10202 case value_t::array:
10203 {
10204 if (add_prefix)
10205 {
10206 oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
10207 }
10208
10209 bool prefix_required = true;
10210 if (use_type and not j.m_value.array->empty())
10211 {
10212 assert(use_count);
10213 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10214 const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
10215 [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
10216 {
10217 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10218 });
10219
10220 if (same_prefix)
10221 {
10222 prefix_required = false;
10223 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10224 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10225 }
10226 }
10227
10228 if (use_count)
10229 {
10230 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10231 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true);
10232 }
10233
10234 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
10235 {
10236 write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10237 }
10238
10239 if (not use_count)
10240 {
10241 oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
10242 }
10243
10244 break;
10245 }
10246
10247 case value_t::object:
10248 {
10249 if (add_prefix)
10250 {
10251 oa->write_character(to_char_type('{'));
10252 }
10253
10254 bool prefix_required = true;
10255 if (use_type and not j.m_value.object->empty())
10256 {
10257 assert(use_count);
10258 const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front());
10259 const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
10260 [this, first_prefix](const BasicJsonType & v)
10261 {
10262 return ubjson_prefix(v) == first_prefix;
10263 });
10264
10265 if (same_prefix)
10266 {
10267 prefix_required = false;
10268 oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
10269 oa->write_character(first_prefix);
10270 }
10271 }
10272
10273 if (use_count)
10274 {
10275 oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
10276 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true);
10277 }
10278
10279 for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
10280 {
10281 write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true);
10282 oa->write_characters(
10283 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
10284 el.first.size());
10285 write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required);
10286 }
10287
10288 if (not use_count)
10289 {
10290 oa->write_character(to_char_type('}'));
10291 }
10292
10293 break;
10294 }
10295
10296 default:
10297 break;
10298 }
10299 }
10300
10301 private:
10303 // BSON //
10305
10310 static std::size_t calc_bson_entry_header_size(const string_t& name)
10311 {
10312 const auto it = name.find(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0));
10313 if (JSON_UNLIKELY(it != BasicJsonType::string_t::npos))
10314 {
10315 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(409,
10316 "BSON key cannot contain code point U+0000 (at byte " + std::to_string(it) + ")"));
10317 }
10318
10319 return /*id*/ 1ul + name.size() + /*zero-terminator*/1u;
10320 }
10321
10325 void write_bson_entry_header(const string_t& name,
10326 const std::uint8_t element_type)
10327 {
10328 oa->write_character(to_char_type(element_type)); // boolean
10329 oa->write_characters(
10330 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(name.c_str()),
10331 name.size() + 1u);
10332 }
10333
10337 void write_bson_boolean(const string_t& name,
10338 const bool value)
10339 {
10340 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x08);
10341 oa->write_character(value ? to_char_type(0x01) : to_char_type(0x00));
10342 }
10343
10347 void write_bson_double(const string_t& name,
10348 const double value)
10349 {
10350 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x01);
10351 write_number<double, true>(value);
10352 }
10353
10357 static std::size_t calc_bson_string_size(const string_t& value)
10358 {
10359 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
10360 }
10361
10365 void write_bson_string(const string_t& name,
10366 const string_t& value)
10367 {
10368 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x02);
10369
10370 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size() + 1ul));
10371 oa->write_characters(
10372 reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.c_str()),
10373 value.size() + 1);
10374 }
10375
10379 void write_bson_null(const string_t& name)
10380 {
10381 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x0A);
10382 }
10383
10387 static std::size_t calc_bson_integer_size(const std::int64_t value)
10388 {
10389 return (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()
10390 ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10391 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10392 }
10393
10397 void write_bson_integer(const string_t& name,
10398 const std::int64_t value)
10399 {
10400 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value and value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10401 {
10402 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10); // int32
10403 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10404 }
10405 else
10406 {
10407 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12); // int64
10408 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10409 }
10410 }
10411
10415 static constexpr std::size_t calc_bson_unsigned_size(const std::uint64_t value) noexcept
10416 {
10417 return (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10418 ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
10419 : sizeof(std::int64_t);
10420 }
10421
10425 void write_bson_unsigned(const string_t& name,
10426 const std::uint64_t value)
10427 {
10428 if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10429 {
10430 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10 /* int32 */);
10431 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value));
10432 }
10433 else if (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
10434 {
10435 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12 /* int64 */);
10436 write_number<std::int64_t, true>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value));
10437 }
10438 else
10439 {
10440 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(value) + " cannot be represented by BSON as it does not fit int64"));
10441 }
10442 }
10443
10447 void write_bson_object_entry(const string_t& name,
10448 const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10449 {
10450 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x03); // object
10451 write_bson_object(value);
10452 }
10453
10457 static std::size_t calc_bson_array_size(const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
10458 {
10459 std::size_t embedded_document_size = 0ul;
10460 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10461
10462 for (const auto& el : value)
10463 {
10464 embedded_document_size += calc_bson_element_size(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10465 }
10466
10467 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + embedded_document_size + 1ul;
10468 }
10469
10473 void write_bson_array(const string_t& name,
10474 const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
10475 {
10476 write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x04); // array
10477 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_array_size(value)));
10478
10479 std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
10480
10481 for (const auto& el : value)
10482 {
10483 write_bson_element(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
10484 }
10485
10486 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10487 }
10488
10493 static std::size_t calc_bson_element_size(const string_t& name,
10494 const BasicJsonType& j)
10495 {
10496 const auto header_size = calc_bson_entry_header_size(name);
10497 switch (j.type())
10498 {
10499 case value_t::object:
10500 return header_size + calc_bson_object_size(*j.m_value.object);
10501
10502 case value_t::array:
10503 return header_size + calc_bson_array_size(*j.m_value.array);
10504
10505 case value_t::boolean:
10506 return header_size + 1ul;
10507
10508 case value_t::number_float:
10509 return header_size + 8ul;
10510
10511 case value_t::number_integer:
10512 return header_size + calc_bson_integer_size(j.m_value.number_integer);
10513
10514 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10515 return header_size + calc_bson_unsigned_size(j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10516
10517 case value_t::string:
10518 return header_size + calc_bson_string_size(*j.m_value.string);
10519
10520 case value_t::null:
10521 return header_size + 0ul;
10522
10523 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10524 default:
10525 assert(false);
10526 return 0ul;
10527 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10528 }
10529 }
10530
10538 void write_bson_element(const string_t& name,
10539 const BasicJsonType& j)
10540 {
10541 switch (j.type())
10542 {
10543 case value_t::object:
10544 return write_bson_object_entry(name, *j.m_value.object);
10545
10546 case value_t::array:
10547 return write_bson_array(name, *j.m_value.array);
10548
10549 case value_t::boolean:
10550 return write_bson_boolean(name, j.m_value.boolean);
10551
10552 case value_t::number_float:
10553 return write_bson_double(name, j.m_value.number_float);
10554
10555 case value_t::number_integer:
10556 return write_bson_integer(name, j.m_value.number_integer);
10557
10558 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10559 return write_bson_unsigned(name, j.m_value.number_unsigned);
10560
10561 case value_t::string:
10562 return write_bson_string(name, *j.m_value.string);
10563
10564 case value_t::null:
10565 return write_bson_null(name);
10566
10567 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10568 default:
10569 assert(false);
10570 return;
10571 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10572 }
10573 }
10574
10581 static std::size_t calc_bson_object_size(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10582 {
10583 std::size_t document_size = std::accumulate(value.begin(), value.end(), 0ul,
10584 [](size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type & el)
10585 {
10586 return result += calc_bson_element_size(el.first, el.second);
10587 });
10588
10589 return sizeof(std::int32_t) + document_size + 1ul;
10590 }
10591
10596 void write_bson_object(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
10597 {
10598 write_number<std::int32_t, true>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_object_size(value)));
10599
10600 for (const auto& el : value)
10601 {
10602 write_bson_element(el.first, el.second);
10603 }
10604
10605 oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
10606 }

10613 {
10614 return to_char_type(0xFA); // Single-Precision Float
10615 }
10616
10617 static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
10618 {
10619 return to_char_type(0xFB); // Double-Precision Float
10620 }

10627 {
10628 return to_char_type(0xCA); // float 32
10629 }
10630
10631 static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
10632 {
10633 return to_char_type(0xCB); // float 64
10634 }

10637 // UBJSON //
10639
10640 // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
10641 template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10642 std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10643 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10644 const bool add_prefix)
10645 {
10646 if (add_prefix)
10647 {
10648 oa->write_character(get_ubjson_float_prefix(n));
10649 }
10650 write_number(n);
10651 }
10652
10653 // UBJSON: write number (unsigned integer)
10654 template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10655 std::is_unsigned<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10656 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10657 const bool add_prefix)
10658 {
10659 if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)()))
10660 {
10661 if (add_prefix)
10662 {
10663 oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
10664 }
10665 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10666 }
10667 else if (n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10668 {
10669 if (add_prefix)
10670 {
10671 oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
10672 }
10673 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10674 }
10675 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)()))
10676 {
10677 if (add_prefix)
10678 {
10679 oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
10680 }
10681 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
10682 }
10683 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
10684 {
10685 if (add_prefix)
10686 {
10687 oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
10688 }
10689 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
10690 }
10691 else if (n <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
10692 {
10693 if (add_prefix)
10694 {
10695 oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
10696 }
10697 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
10698 }
10699 else
10700 {
10701 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(n) + " cannot be represented by UBJSON as it does not fit int64"));
10702 }
10703 }
10704
10705 // UBJSON: write number (signed integer)
10706 template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
10707 std::is_signed<NumberType>::value and
10708 not std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
10709 void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
10710 const bool add_prefix)
10711 {
10712 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10713 {
10714 if (add_prefix)
10715 {
10716 oa->write_character(to_char_type('i')); // int8
10717 }
10718 write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(n));
10719 }
10720 else if (static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)()) <= n and n <= static_cast<std::int64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)()))
10721 {
10722 if (add_prefix)
10723 {
10724 oa->write_character(to_char_type('U')); // uint8
10725 }
10726 write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(n));
10727 }
10728 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10729 {
10730 if (add_prefix)
10731 {
10732 oa->write_character(to_char_type('I')); // int16
10733 }
10734 write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(n));
10735 }
10736 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10737 {
10738 if (add_prefix)
10739 {
10740 oa->write_character(to_char_type('l')); // int32
10741 }
10742 write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(n));
10743 }
10744 else if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() <= n and n <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
10745 {
10746 if (add_prefix)
10747 {
10748 oa->write_character(to_char_type('L')); // int64
10749 }
10750 write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(n));
10751 }
10752 // LCOV_EXCL_START
10753 else
10754 {
10755 JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, "integer number " + std::to_string(n) + " cannot be represented by UBJSON as it does not fit int64"));
10756 }
10757 // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
10758 }
10759
10769 CharType ubjson_prefix(const BasicJsonType& j) const noexcept
10770 {
10771 switch (j.type())
10772 {
10773 case value_t::null:
10774 return 'Z';
10775
10776 case value_t::boolean:
10777 return j.m_value.boolean ? 'T' : 'F';
10778
10779 case value_t::number_integer:
10780 {
10781 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10782 {
10783 return 'i';
10784 }
10785 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10786 {
10787 return 'U';
10788 }
10789 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10790 {
10791 return 'I';
10792 }
10793 if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= j.m_value.number_integer and j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10794 {
10795 return 'l';
10796 }
10797 // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
10798 return 'L';
10799 }
10800
10801 case value_t::number_unsigned:
10802 {
10803 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
10804 {
10805 return 'i';
10806 }
10807 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
10808 {
10809 return 'U';
10810 }
10811 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
10812 {
10813 return 'I';
10814 }
10815 if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
10816 {
10817 return 'l';
10818 }
10819 // no check and assume int64_t (see note above)
10820 return 'L';
10821 }
10822
10823 case value_t::number_float:
10824 return get_ubjson_float_prefix(j.m_value.number_float);
10825
10826 case value_t::string:
10827 return 'S';
10828
10829 case value_t::array:
10830 return '[';
10831
10832 case value_t::object:
10833 return '{';
10834
10835 default: // discarded values
10836 return 'N';
10837 }
10838 }
10839
10840 static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
10841 {
10842 return 'd'; // float 32
10843 }
10844
10845 static constexpr CharType get_ubjson_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
10846 {
10847 return 'D'; // float 64
10848 }
10849
10851 // Utility functions //
10853
10854 /*
10855 @brief write a number to output input
10856 @param[in] n number of type @a NumberType
10857 @tparam NumberType the type of the number
10858 @tparam OutputIsLittleEndian Set to true if output data is
10859 required to be little endian
10860
10861 @note This function needs to respect the system's endianess, because bytes
10862 in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order (big
10863 endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
10864 */
10865 template<typename NumberType, bool OutputIsLittleEndian = false>
10866 void write_number(const NumberType n)
10867 {
10868 // step 1: write number to array of length NumberType
10869 std::array<CharType, sizeof(NumberType)> vec;
10870 std::memcpy(vec.data(), &n, sizeof(NumberType));
10871
10872 // step 2: write array to output (with possible reordering)
10873 if (is_little_endian != OutputIsLittleEndian)
10874 {
10875 // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
10876 std::reverse(vec.begin(), vec.end());
10877 }
10878
10879 oa->write_characters(vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
10880 }
10881
10882 public:
10883 // The following to_char_type functions are implement the conversion
10884 // between uint8_t and CharType. In case CharType is not unsigned,
10885 // such a conversion is required to allow values greater than 128.
10886 // See <https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1286> for a discussion.
10887 template < typename C = CharType,
10888 enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value and std::is_signed<char>::value > * = nullptr >
10889 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10890 {
10891 return *reinterpret_cast<char*>(&x);
10892 }
10893
10894 template < typename C = CharType,
10895 enable_if_t < std::is_signed<C>::value and std::is_unsigned<char>::value > * = nullptr >
10896 static CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10897 {
10898 static_assert(sizeof(std::uint8_t) == sizeof(CharType), "size of CharType must be equal to std::uint8_t");
10899 static_assert(std::is_pod<CharType>::value, "CharType must be POD");
10900 CharType result;
10901 std::memcpy(&result, &x, sizeof(x));
10902 return result;
10903 }
10904
10905 template<typename C = CharType,
10906 enable_if_t<std::is_unsigned<C>::value>* = nullptr>
10907 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(std::uint8_t x) noexcept
10908 {
10909 return x;
10910 }
10911
10912 template < typename InputCharType, typename C = CharType,
10913 enable_if_t <
10914 std::is_signed<C>::value and
10915 std::is_signed<char>::value and
10916 std::is_same<char, typename std::remove_cv<InputCharType>::type>::value
10917 > * = nullptr >
10918 static constexpr CharType to_char_type(InputCharType x) noexcept
10919 {
10920 return x;
10921 }
10922
10923 private:
10925 const bool is_little_endian = binary_reader<BasicJsonType>::little_endianess();
10926
10928 output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
10929 };
10930 } // namespace detail
10931} // namespace nlohmann
